82 
83 // DEFINING NEW OPERATIONS
84 // =======================
85 // For each operation `Foo`, we define:
86 // - An entry V(Foo) in one of the TURBOSHAFT*OPERATION list (eg,
87 // TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST_BLOCK_TERMINATOR,
88 // TURBOSHAFT_SIMPLIFIED_OPERATION_LIST etc), which defines
89 // `Opcode::kFoo` and whether the operation is a block terminator.
90 // - A `struct FooOp`, which derives from either `OperationT<FooOp>` or
91 // `FixedArityOperationT<k, FooOp>` if the op always has excactly `k` inputs.
92 // Furthermore, the struct has to contain:
93 // - A bunch of options directly as public fields.
94 // - A getter `options()` returning a tuple of all these options. This is used
95 // for default printing and hashing. Alternatively, `void
96 // PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const` and `size_t hash_value() const` can
97 // also be defined manually.
98 // - Getters for named inputs.
99 // - A constructor that first takes all the inputs and then all the options. For
100 // a variable arity operation where the constructor doesn't take the inputs as
101 // a single base::Vector<OpIndex> argument, it's also necessary to overwrite
102 // the static `New` function, see `CallOp` for an example.
103 // - An `Explode` method that unpacks an operation and invokes the passed
104 // callback. If the operation inherits from FixedArityOperationT, the base
105 // class already provides the required implementation.
106 // - `OpEffects` as either a static constexpr member `effects` or a
107 // non-static method `Effects()` if the effects depend on the particular
108 // operation and not just the opcode.
109 // - outputs_rep/inputs_rep methods, which should return a vector describing the
110 // representation of the outputs and inputs of this operations.
111 // After defining the struct here, you'll also need to integrate it in
112 // Turboshaft:
113 // - If Foo is not lowered before reaching the instruction selector, handle
114 // Opcode::kFoo in the Turboshaft VisitNode of instruction-selector.cc.
115

120 #endif // V8_INTL_SUPPORT

408 #define COUNT_OPCODES(Name) +1

410  0 TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST_BLOCK_TERMINATOR(COUNT_OPCODES);
411 #undef COUNT_OPCODES

413 #define COUNT_OPCODES(Name) +1

418 inline constexpr bool IsBlockTerminator(Opcode opcode) {
419  return OpcodeIndex(opcode) < kNumberOfBlockTerminatorOpcodes;
420 }

433 // Operations that need to be followed by `DidntThrowOp`.
434 inline constexpr bool MayThrow(Opcode opcode) {
435 #define CASE(Name) case Opcode::k##Name:
436  switch (opcode) {
437  TURBOSHAFT_THROWING_OPERATIONS_LIST(CASE)
438  return true;
439  default:
440  return false;
441  }
442 #undef CASE
443 }
444 
445 // For Throwing operations, outputs_rep() are empty, because the values are
446 // produced by the subsequent DidntThrow. Nevertheless, the operation has to
447 // define its output representations in an array that DidntThrow can then reuse
448 // to know what its outputs are. Additionally, when using Maglev as a frontend,
449 // catch handlers that have never been reach so far are not emitted, and instead
450 // the throwing operations lazy deopt instead of throwing.
451 //
452 // That's where the THROWING_OP_BOILERPLATE macro comes in: it creates an array
453 // of representations that DidntThrow can use, and will define outputs_rep() to
454 // be empty, and takes care of creating a LazyDeoptOnThrow member. For instance:
455 //
456 // THROWING_OP_BOILERPLATE(RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
457 // RegisterRepresentation::Word32())
458 //
459 // Warning: don't forget to add `lazy_deopt_on_throw` to the `options` of your
460 // Operation (you'll get a compile-time error if you forget it).
461 #define THROWING_OP_BOILERPLATE(...) \
462  static constexpr RegisterRepresentation kOutputRepsStorage[]{__VA_ARGS__}; \
463  static constexpr base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> kOutReps = \
464  base::VectorOf(kOutputRepsStorage, arraysize(kOutputRepsStorage)); \
465  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { \
466  return {}; \
467  } \
468  LazyDeoptOnThrow lazy_deopt_on_throw;
469 
470 template <typename T>
471 inline base::Vector<T> InitVectorOf(
472  ZoneVector<T>& storage,
473  std::initializer_list<RegisterRepresentation> values) {
474  storage.resize(values.size());
475  size_t i = 0;
476  for (auto&& value : values) {
477  storage[i++] = value;
478  }
479  return base::VectorOf(storage);
480 }
481 
482 class InputsRepFactory {
483  public:
484  constexpr static base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> SingleRep(
485  RegisterRepresentation rep) {
486  return base::VectorOf(ToMaybeRepPointer(rep), 1);
487  }
488 
489  constexpr static base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> PairOf(
490  RegisterRepresentation rep) {
491  return base::VectorOf(ToMaybeRepPointer(rep), 2);
492  }
493 
494  protected:
495  constexpr static const MaybeRegisterRepresentation* ToMaybeRepPointer(
496  RegisterRepresentation rep) {
497  size_t index = static_cast<size_t>(rep.value()) * 2;
498  DCHECK_LT(index, arraysize(rep_map));
499  return &rep_map[index];
500  }
501 
502  private:
503  constexpr static MaybeRegisterRepresentation rep_map[] = {
504  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32(),
505  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32(),
506  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word64(),
507  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word64(),
508  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Float32(),
509  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Float32(),
510  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Float64(),
511  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Float64(),
512  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
513  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
514  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Compressed(),
515  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Compressed(),
516  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Simd128(),
517  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Simd128(),
518 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
519  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Simd256(),
520  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Simd256(),
521 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
522  };
523 };
524 
525 struct EffectDimensions {
526  // Produced by loads, consumed by operations that should not move before loads
527  // because they change memory.
528  bool load_heap_memory : 1;
529  bool load_off_heap_memory : 1;
530 
531  // Produced by stores, consumed by operations that should not move before
532  // stores because they load or store memory.
533  bool store_heap_memory : 1;
534  bool store_off_heap_memory : 1;
535 
536  // Operations that perform raw heap access (like initialization) consume
537  // `before_raw_heap_access` and produce `after_raw_heap_access`.
538  // Operations that need the heap to be in a consistent state produce
539  // `before_raw_heap_access` and consume `after_raw_heap_access`.
540  bool before_raw_heap_access : 1;
541  // Produced by operations that access raw/untagged pointers into the
542  // heap or keep such a pointer alive, consumed by operations that can GC to
543  // ensure they don't move before the raw access.
544  bool after_raw_heap_access : 1;
545 
546  // Produced by any operation that can affect whether subsequent operations are
547  // executed, for example by branching, deopting, throwing or aborting.
548  // Consumed by all operations that should not be hoisted before a check
549  // because they rely on it. For example, loads usually rely on the shape of
550  // the heap object or the index being in bounds.
551  bool control_flow : 1;
552  // We need to ensure that the padding bits have a specified value, as they are
553  // observable in bitwise operations.
554  uint8_t unused_padding : 1;
555 
556  using Bits = uint8_t;
557  constexpr EffectDimensions()
558  : load_heap_memory(false),
559  load_off_heap_memory(false),
560  store_heap_memory(false),
561  store_off_heap_memory(false),
562  before_raw_heap_access(false),
563  after_raw_heap_access(false),
564  control_flow(false),
565  unused_padding(0) {}
566  Bits bits() const { return base::bit_cast<Bits>(*this); }
567  static EffectDimensions FromBits(Bits bits) {
568  return base::bit_cast<EffectDimensions>(bits);
569  }
570  bool operator==(EffectDimensions other) const {
571  return bits() == other.bits();
572  }
573  bool operator!=(EffectDimensions other) const {
574  return bits() != other.bits();
575  }
576 };
577 static_assert(sizeof(EffectDimensions) == sizeof(EffectDimensions::Bits));
578 
579 // Possible reorderings are restricted using two bit vectors: `produces` and
580 // `consumes`. Two operations cannot be reordered if the first operation
581 // produces an effect dimension that the second operation consumes. This is not
582 // necessarily symmetric. For example, it is possible to reorder
583 // Load(x)
584 // CheckMaps(y)
585 // to become
586 // CheckMaps(x)
587 // Load(y)
588 // because the load cannot affect the map check. But the other direction could
589 // be unsound, if the load depends on the map check having been executed. The
590 // former reordering is useful to push a load across a check into a branch if
591 // it is only needed there. The effect system expresses this by having the map
592 // check produce `EffectDimensions::control_flow` and the load consuming
593 // `EffectDimensions::control_flow`. If the producing operation comes before the
594 // consuming operation, then this order has to be preserved. But if the
595 // consuming operation comes first, then we are free to reorder them. Operations
596 // that produce and consume the same effect dimension always have a fixed order
597 // among themselves. For example, stores produce and consume the store
598 // dimensions. It is possible for operations to be reorderable unless certain
599 // other operations appear in-between. This way, the IR can be generous with
600 // reorderings as long as all operations are high-level, but become more
601 // restrictive as soon as low-level operations appear. For example, allocations
602 // can be freely reordered. Tagged bitcasts can be reordered with other tagged
603 // bitcasts. But a tagged bitcast cannot be reordered with allocations, as this
604 // would mean that an untagged pointer can be alive while a GC is happening. The
605 // way this works is that allocations produce the `before_raw_heap_access`
606 // dimension and consume the `after_raw_heap_access` dimension to stay either
607 // before or after a raw heap access. This means that there are no ordering
608 // constraints between allocations themselves. Bitcasts should not
609 // be moved accross an allocation. We treat them as raw heap access by letting
610 // them consume `before_raw_heap_access` and produce `after_raw_heap_access`.
611 // This way, allocations cannot be moved across bitcasts. Similarily,
612 // initializing stores and uninitialized allocations are classified as raw heap
613 // access, to prevent any operation that relies on a consistent heap state to be
614 // scheduled in the middle of an inline allocation. As long as we didn't lower
615 // to raw heap accesses yet, pure allocating operations or operations reading
616 // immutable memory can float freely. As soon as there are raw heap accesses,
617 // they become more restricted in their movement. Note that calls are not the
618 // most side-effectful operations, as they do not leave the heap in an
619 // inconsistent state, so they do not need to be marked as raw heap access.
620 struct OpEffects {
621  EffectDimensions produces;
622  EffectDimensions consumes;
623 
624  // Operations that cannot be merged because they produce identity. That is,
625  // every repetition can produce a different result, but the order in which
626  // they are executed does not matter. All we care about is that they are
627  // different. Producing a random number or allocating an object with
628  // observable pointer equality are examples. Producing identity doesn't
629  // restrict reordering in straight-line code, but we must prevent using GVN or
630  // moving identity-producing operations in- or out of loops.
631  bool can_create_identity : 1;
632  // If the operation can allocate and therefore can trigger GC.
633  bool can_allocate : 1;
634  // Instructions that have no uses but are `required_when_unused` should not be
635  // removed.
636  bool required_when_unused : 1;
637  // We need to ensure that the padding bits have a specified value, as they are
638  // observable in bitwise operations. This is split into two fields so that
639  // also MSVC creates the correct object layout.
640  uint8_t unused_padding_1 : 5;
641  uint8_t unused_padding_2;
642 
643  constexpr OpEffects()
644  : can_create_identity(false),
645  can_allocate(false),
646  required_when_unused(false),
647  unused_padding_1(0),
648  unused_padding_2(0) {}
649 
650  using Bits = uint32_t;
651  Bits bits() const { return base::bit_cast<Bits>(*this); }
652  static OpEffects FromBits(Bits bits) {
653  return base::bit_cast<OpEffects>(bits);
654  }
655 
656  bool operator==(OpEffects other) const { return bits() == other.bits(); }
657  bool operator!=(OpEffects other) const { return bits() != other.bits(); }
658  OpEffects operator|(OpEffects other) const {
659  return FromBits(bits() | other.bits());
660  }
661  OpEffects operator&(OpEffects other) const {
662  return FromBits(bits() & other.bits());
663  }
664  bool IsSubsetOf(OpEffects other) const {
665  return (bits() & ~other.bits()) == 0;
666  }
667 
668  constexpr OpEffects AssumesConsistentHeap() const {
669  OpEffects result = *this;
670  // Do not move the operation into a region with raw heap access.
671  result.produces.before_raw_heap_access = true;
672  result.consumes.after_raw_heap_access = true;
673  return result;
674  }
675  // Like `CanAllocate()`, but allocated values must be immutable and not have
676  // identity (for example `HeapNumber`).
677  // Note that if we first allocate something as mutable and later make it
678  // immutable, we have to allocate it with identity.
679  constexpr OpEffects CanAllocateWithoutIdentity() const {
680  OpEffects result = AssumesConsistentHeap();
681  result.can_allocate = true;
682  return result;
683  }
684  // Allocations change the GC state and can trigger GC, as well as produce a
685  // fresh identity.
686  constexpr OpEffects CanAllocate() const {
687  return CanAllocateWithoutIdentity().CanCreateIdentity();
688  }
689  // The operation can leave the heap in an incosistent state or have untagged
690  // pointers into the heap as input or output.
691  constexpr OpEffects CanDoRawHeapAccess() const {
692  OpEffects result = *this;
693  // Do not move any operation that relies on a consistent heap state accross.
694  result.produces.after_raw_heap_access = true;
695  result.consumes.before_raw_heap_access = true;
696  return result;
697  }
698  // Reading mutable heap memory. Reading immutable memory doesn't count.
699  constexpr OpEffects CanReadHeapMemory() const {
700  OpEffects result = *this;
701  result.produces.load_heap_memory = true;
702  // Do not reorder before stores.
703  result.consumes.store_heap_memory = true;
704  return result;
705  }
706  // Reading mutable off-heap memory or other input. Reading immutable memory
707  // doesn't count.
708  constexpr OpEffects CanReadOffHeapMemory() const {
709  OpEffects result = *this;
710  result.produces.load_off_heap_memory = true;
711  // Do not reorder before stores.
712  result.consumes.store_off_heap_memory = true;
713  return result;
714  }
715  // Writing any off-memory or other output.
716  constexpr OpEffects CanWriteOffHeapMemory() const {
717  OpEffects result = *this;
718  result.required_when_unused = true;
719  result.produces.store_off_heap_memory = true;
720  // Do not reorder before stores.
721  result.consumes.store_off_heap_memory = true;
722  // Do not reorder before loads.
723  result.consumes.load_off_heap_memory = true;
724  // Do not move before deopting or aborting operations.
725  result.consumes.control_flow = true;
726  return result;
727  }
728  // Writing heap memory that existed before the operation started. Initializing
729  // newly allocated memory doesn't count.
730  constexpr OpEffects CanWriteHeapMemory() const {
731  OpEffects result = *this;
732  result.required_when_unused = true;
733  result.produces.store_heap_memory = true;
734  // Do not reorder before stores.
735  result.consumes.store_heap_memory = true;
736  // Do not reorder before loads.
737  result.consumes.load_heap_memory = true;
738  // Do not move before deopting or aborting operations.
739  result.consumes.control_flow = true;
740  return result;
741  }
742  // Writing any memory or other output, on- or off-heap.
743  constexpr OpEffects CanWriteMemory() const {
744  return CanWriteHeapMemory().CanWriteOffHeapMemory();
745  }
746  // Reading any memory or other input, on- or off-heap.
747  constexpr OpEffects CanReadMemory() const {
748  return CanReadHeapMemory().CanReadOffHeapMemory();
749  }
750  // The operation might read immutable data from the heap, so it can be freely
751  // reordered with operations that keep the heap in a consistent state. But we
752  // must prevent the operation from observing an incompletely initialized
753  // object.
754  constexpr OpEffects CanReadImmutableMemory() const {
755  OpEffects result = AssumesConsistentHeap();
756  return result;
757  }
758  // Partial operations that are only safe to execute after we performed certain
759  // checks, for example loads may only be safe after a corresponding bound or
760  // map checks.
761  constexpr OpEffects CanDependOnChecks() const {
762  OpEffects result = *this;
763  result.consumes.control_flow = true;
764  return result;
765  }
766  // The operation can affect control flow (like branch, deopt, throw or crash).
767  constexpr OpEffects CanChangeControlFlow() const {
768  OpEffects result = *this;
769  result.required_when_unused = true;
770  // Signal that this changes control flow. Prevents stores or operations
771  // relying on checks from flowing before this operation.
772  result.produces.control_flow = true;
773  // Stores must not flow past something that affects control flow.
774  result.consumes.store_heap_memory = true;
775  result.consumes.store_off_heap_memory = true;
776  return result;
777  }
778  // Execution of the current function may end with this operation, for example
779  // because of return, deopt, exception throw or abort/trap.
780  constexpr OpEffects CanLeaveCurrentFunction() const {
781  // All memory becomes observable.
782  return CanChangeControlFlow().CanReadMemory().RequiredWhenUnused();
783  }
784  // The operation can deopt.
785  constexpr OpEffects CanDeopt() const {
786  return CanLeaveCurrentFunction()
787  // We might depend on previous checks to avoid deopting.
788  .CanDependOnChecks();
789  }
790  // Producing identity doesn't prevent reorderings, but it prevents GVN from
791  // de-duplicating identical operations.
792  constexpr OpEffects CanCreateIdentity() const {
793  OpEffects result = *this;
794  result.can_create_identity = true;
795  return result;
796  }
797  // The set of all possible effects.
798  constexpr OpEffects CanCallAnything() const {
799  return CanReadMemory()
800  .CanWriteMemory()
801  .CanAllocate()
802  .CanChangeControlFlow()
803  .CanDependOnChecks()
804  .RequiredWhenUnused();
805  }
806  constexpr OpEffects RequiredWhenUnused() const {
807  OpEffects result = *this;
808  result.required_when_unused = true;
809  return result;
810  }
811 
812  // Operations that can be removed if their result is not used. Unused
813  // allocations can be removed.
814  constexpr bool is_required_when_unused() const {
815  return required_when_unused;
816  }
817  // Operations that can be moved before a preceding branch or check.
818  bool hoistable_before_a_branch() const {
819  // Since this excludes `CanDependOnChecks()`, most loads actually cannot be
820  // hoisted.
821  return IsSubsetOf(OpEffects().CanReadMemory());
822  }
823  bool can_read_mutable_memory() const {
824  return produces.load_heap_memory | produces.load_off_heap_memory;
825  }
826  bool requires_consistent_heap() const {
827  return produces.before_raw_heap_access | consumes.after_raw_heap_access;
828  }
829  bool can_write() const {
830  return produces.store_heap_memory | produces.store_off_heap_memory;
831  }
832  bool can_be_constant_folded() const {
833  // Operations that CanDependOnChecks can still be constant-folded. If they
834  // did indeed depend on a check, then their result will only be used after
835  // said check has been executed anyways.
836  return IsSubsetOf(OpEffects().CanDependOnChecks());
837  }
838 };
839 static_assert(sizeof(OpEffects) == sizeof(OpEffects::Bits));
840 
841 V8_INLINE size_t hash_value(OpEffects effects) {
842  return static_cast<size_t>(effects.bits());
843 }
844 
845 inline bool CannotSwapOperations(OpEffects first, OpEffects second) {
846  return first.produces.bits() & (second.consumes.bits());
847 }
848 
849 inline bool CannotSwapProtectedLoads(OpEffects first, OpEffects second) {
850  EffectDimensions produces = first.produces;
851  // The control flow effects produced by Loads are due to trap handler. We can
852  // ignore this kind of effect when swapping two Loads that both have trap
853  // handler.
854  produces.control_flow = false;
855  return produces.bits() & (second.consumes.bits());
856 }
857 
858 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os,
859  OpEffects op_effects);
860 
861 // SaturatedUint8 is a wrapper around a uint8_t, which can be incremented and
862 // decremented with the `Incr` and `Decr` methods. These methods prevent over-
863 // and underflow, and saturate once the uint8_t reaches the maximum (255):
864 // future increment and decrement will not change the value then.
865 // We purposefuly do not expose the uint8_t directly, so that users go through
866 // Incr/Decr/SetToZero/SetToOne to manipulate it, so that the saturation and
867 // lack of over/underflow is always respected.
868 class SaturatedUint8 {
869  public:
870  SaturatedUint8() = default;
871 
872  void Incr() {
873  if (V8_LIKELY(val != kMax)) {
874  val++;
875  }
876  }
877  void Decr() {
878  if (V8_LIKELY(val != 0 && val != kMax)) {
879  val--;
880  }
881  }
882 
883  void SetToZero() { val = 0; }
884  void SetToOne() { val = 1; }
885 
886  bool IsZero() const { return val == 0; }
887  bool IsOne() const { return val == 1; }
888  bool IsSaturated() const { return val == kMax; }
889  uint8_t Get() const { return val; }
890 
891  SaturatedUint8& operator+=(const SaturatedUint8& other) {
892  uint32_t sum = val;
893  sum += other.val;
894  val = static_cast<uint8_t>(std::min<uint32_t>(sum, kMax));
895  return *this;
896  }
897 
898  static SaturatedUint8 FromSize(size_t value) {
899  uint8_t val = static_cast<uint8_t>(std::min<size_t>(value, kMax));
900  return SaturatedUint8{val};
901  }
902 
903  private:
904  explicit SaturatedUint8(uint8_t val) : val(val) {}
905  uint8_t val = 0;
906  static constexpr uint8_t kMax = std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max();
907 };
908 
909 // underlying_operation<> is used to extract the operation type from OpMaskT
910 // classes used in Operation::Is<> and Operation::TryCast<>.
911 template <typename T>
912 struct underlying_operation {
913  using type = T;
914 };
915 template <typename T, uint64_t M, uint64_t V>
916 struct underlying_operation<OpMaskT<T, M, V>> {
917  using type = T;
918 };
919 template <typename T>
920 using underlying_operation_t = typename underlying_operation<T>::type;

922 // Baseclass for all Turboshaft operations.
923 // The `alignas(OpIndex)` is necessary because it is followed by an array of
924 // `OpIndex` inputs.
925 struct alignas(OpIndex) Operation {
926  struct IdentityMapper {
927  OpIndex Map(OpIndex index) { return index; }
928  OptionalOpIndex Map(OptionalOpIndex index) { return index; }
929  template <size_t N>
930  base::SmallVector<OpIndex, N> Map(base::Vector<const OpIndex> indices) {
931  return base::SmallVector<OpIndex, N>{indices};
932  }
933  };
934 
935  const Opcode opcode;
936 
937  // The number of uses of this operation in the current graph.
938  // Instead of overflowing, we saturate the value if it reaches the maximum. In
939  // this case, the true number of uses is unknown.
940  // We use such a small type to save memory and because nodes with a high
941  // number of uses are rare. Additionally, we usually only care if the number
942  // of uses is 0, 1 or bigger than 1.
943  SaturatedUint8 saturated_use_count;
944 
945  const uint16_t input_count;
946 
947  // The inputs are stored adjacent in memory, right behind the `Operation`
948  // object.
949  base::Vector<const OpIndex> inputs() const;
950  V8_INLINE OpIndex input(size_t i) const { return inputs()[i]; }
951 
952  static size_t StorageSlotCount(Opcode opcode, size_t input_count);
953  size_t StorageSlotCount() const {
954  return StorageSlotCount(opcode, input_count);
955  }

958  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
959  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const;

961  template <class Op>
962  bool Is() const {
963  if constexpr (std::is_base_of_v<Operation, Op>) {
964  return opcode == Op::opcode;
965  } else {
966  // Otherwise this must be OpMaskT.
967  return IsOpmask<Op>();
968  }
969  }
970  template <class Op>
971  underlying_operation_t<Op>& Cast() {
972  DCHECK(Is<Op>());
973  return *static_cast<underlying_operation_t<Op>*>(this);
974  }
975  template <class Op>
976  const underlying_operation_t<Op>& Cast() const {
977  DCHECK(Is<Op>());
978  return *static_cast<const underlying_operation_t<Op>*>(this);
979  }
980  template <class Op>
981  const underlying_operation_t<Op>* TryCast() const {
982  if (!Is<Op>()) return nullptr;
983  return static_cast<const underlying_operation_t<Op>*>(this);
984  }
985  template <class Op>
986  underlying_operation_t<Op>* TryCast() {
987  if (!Is<Op>()) return nullptr;
988  return static_cast<underlying_operation_t<Op>*>(this);
989  }
990  OpEffects Effects() const;
991  bool IsBlockTerminator() const {
992  return turboshaft::IsBlockTerminator(opcode);
993  }
994  bool IsRequiredWhenUnused() const {
995  DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsBlockTerminator(), Effects().is_required_when_unused());
996  return Effects().is_required_when_unused();
997  }
998  bool IsProtectedLoad() const;
999 
1000  std::string ToString() const;
1001  void PrintInputs(std::ostream& os, const std::string& op_index_prefix) const;
1002  void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
1003 
1004  // Returns true if {this} is the only operation using {value}.
1005  bool IsOnlyUserOf(const Operation& value, const Graph& graph) const;
1006 
1007  void Print() const;
1008 
1009  protected:
1010  // Operation objects store their inputs behind the object. Therefore, they can
1011  // only be constructed as part of a Graph.
1012  explicit Operation(Opcode opcode, size_t input_count)
1013  : opcode(opcode), input_count(input_count) {
1014  DCHECK_LE(input_count,
1015  std::numeric_limits<decltype(this->input_count)>::max());
1016  }
1017 
1018  template <class OpmaskT>
1019  // A Turboshaft operation can be as small as 4 Bytes while Opmasks can span up
1020  // to 8 Bytes. Any mask larger than the operation it is compared with will
1021  // always have a mismatch in the initialized memory. Still, there can be some
1022  // uninitialized memory being compared as part of the 8 Byte comparison that
1023  // this function performs.
1024  V8_CLANG_NO_SANITIZE("memory") bool IsOpmask() const {
1025  static_assert(std::is_same_v<
1026  underlying_operation_t<OpmaskT>,
1027  typename OpMaskT<typename OpmaskT::operation, OpmaskT::mask,
1028  OpmaskT::value>::operation>);
1029  // We check with the given mask.
1030  uint64_t b;
1031  memcpy(&b, this, sizeof(uint64_t));
1032  b &= OpmaskT::mask;
1033  return b == OpmaskT::value;
1034  }
1035 
1036  Operation(const Operation&) = delete;
1037  Operation& operator=(const Operation&) = delete;
1038 };

1048  return os << OperationPrintStyle{op};

1057 // Determine if an operation declares `effects`, which means that its
1058 // effects are static and don't depend on inputs or options.
1059 template <class Op, class = void>
1060 struct HasStaticEffects : std::bool_constant<false> {};
1061 template <class Op>
1062 struct HasStaticEffects<Op, std::void_t<decltype(Op::effects)>>
1063  : std::bool_constant<true> {};
1064 
1065 // This template knows the complete type of the operation and is plugged into
1066 // the inheritance hierarchy. It removes boilerplate from the concrete
1067 // `Operation` subclasses, defining everything that can be expressed
1068 // generically. It overshadows many methods from `Operation` with ones that
1069 // exploit additional static information.
1070 template <class Derived>
1071 struct OperationT : Operation {
1072  // Enable concise base-constructor call in derived struct.
1073  using Base = OperationT;
1074 
1075  static const Opcode opcode;
1076 
1077  static constexpr OpEffects Effects() { return Derived::effects; }
1078  static constexpr bool IsBlockTerminator() {
1079  return turboshaft::IsBlockTerminator(opcode);
1080  }
1081  bool IsRequiredWhenUnused() const {
1082  return IsBlockTerminator() ||
1083  derived_this().Effects().is_required_when_unused();
1084  }
1085 
1086  static constexpr std::optional<OpEffects> EffectsIfStatic() {
1087  if constexpr (HasStaticEffects<Derived>::value) {
1088  return Derived::Effects();
1089  }
1090  return std::nullopt;
1091  }
1092 
1093  Derived& derived_this() { return *static_cast<Derived*>(this); }
1094  const Derived& derived_this() const {
1095  return *static_cast<const Derived*>(this);
1096  }
1097 
1098  // Shadow Operation::inputs to exploit static knowledge about object size.
1099  base::Vector<OpIndex> inputs() {
1100  return {reinterpret_cast<OpIndex*>(reinterpret_cast<char*>(this) +
1101  sizeof(Derived)),
1102  derived_this().input_count};
1103  }
1104  base::Vector<const OpIndex> inputs() const {
1105  return {reinterpret_cast<const OpIndex*>(
1106  reinterpret_cast<const char*>(this) + sizeof(Derived)),
1107  derived_this().input_count};
1108  }
1109 
1110  V8_INLINE OpIndex& input(size_t i) { return derived_this().inputs()[i]; }
1111  // TODO(chromium:331100916): remove this V<Any> overload once all users use
1112  // the more specific V<T> overload.
1113  V8_INLINE V<Any> input(size_t i) const { return derived_this().inputs()[i]; }
1114  template <typename T>
1115  V8_INLINE V<T> input(size_t i) const {
1116  return V<T>::Cast(derived_this().inputs()[i]);
1117  }
1118 
1119  static size_t StorageSlotCount(size_t input_count) {
1120  // The operation size in bytes is:
1121  // `sizeof(Derived) + input_count*sizeof(OpIndex)`.
1122  // This is an optimized computation of:
1123  // round_up(size_in_bytes / sizeof(StorageSlot))
1124  constexpr size_t r = sizeof(OperationStorageSlot) / sizeof(OpIndex);
1125  static_assert(sizeof(OperationStorageSlot) % sizeof(OpIndex) == 0);
1126  static_assert(sizeof(Derived) % sizeof(OpIndex) == 0);
1127  size_t result = std::max<size_t>(
1128  2, (r - 1 + sizeof(Derived) / sizeof(OpIndex) + input_count) / r);
1129  DCHECK_EQ(result, Operation::StorageSlotCount(opcode, input_count));
1130  return result;
1131  }
1132  size_t StorageSlotCount() const { return StorageSlotCount(input_count); }
1133 
1134  template <class... Args>
1135  static Derived& New(Graph* graph, size_t input_count, Args... args) {
1136  OperationStorageSlot* ptr =
1137  AllocateOpStorage(graph, StorageSlotCount(input_count));
1138  Derived* result = new (ptr) Derived(args...);
1139 #ifdef DEBUG
1140  result->Validate(*graph);
1141  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation> storage(get_zone(graph));
1142  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> expected =
1143  result->inputs_rep(storage);
1144  // TODO(mliedtke): DCHECK that expected and inputs are of the same size
1145  // and adapt inputs_rep() to always emit a representation for all inputs.
1146  size_t end = std::min<size_t>(expected.size(), result->input_count);
1147  for (size_t i = 0; i < end; ++i) {
1148  if (expected[i] == MaybeRegisterRepresentation::None()) continue;
1149  ValidateOpInputRep(*graph, result->inputs()[i],
1150  RegisterRepresentation(expected[i]), result);
1151  }
1152 #endif
1153  // If this DCHECK fails, then the number of inputs specified in the
1154  // operation constructor and in the static New function disagree.
1155  DCHECK_EQ(input_count, result->Operation::input_count);
1156  return *result;
1157  }
1158 
1159  template <class... Args>
1160  static Derived& New(Graph* graph, ShadowyOpIndexVectorWrapper inputs,
1161  Args... args) {
1162  return New(graph, inputs.size(), inputs, args...);
1163  }
1164 
1165  explicit OperationT(size_t input_count) : Operation(opcode, input_count) {
1166  static_assert((std::is_base_of_v<OperationT, Derived>));
1167 #if !V8_CC_MSVC
1168  static_assert(std::is_trivially_copyable_v<Derived>);
1169 #endif // !V8_CC_MSVC
1170  static_assert(std::is_trivially_destructible_v<Derived>);
1171  }
1172  explicit OperationT(ShadowyOpIndexVectorWrapper inputs)
1173  : OperationT(inputs.size()) {
1174  this->inputs().OverwriteWith(
1175  static_cast<base::Vector<const OpIndex>>(inputs));
1176  }
1177 
1178  bool EqualsForGVN(const Base& other) const {
1179  // By default, GVN only removed identical Operations. However, some
1180  // Operations (like DeoptimizeIf) can be GVNed when a dominating
1181  // similar-but-not-identical one exists. In that case, the Operation should
1182  // redefine EqualsForGVN, so that GVN knows which inputs or options of the
1183  // Operation to ignore (you should also probably redefine hash_value,
1184  // otherwise GVN won't even try to call EqualsForGVN).
1185  return derived_this() == other.derived_this();
1186  }
1187  bool operator==(const Base& other) const {
1188  return derived_this().inputs() == other.derived_this().inputs() &&
1189  derived_this().options() == other.derived_this().options();
1190  }
1191  template <typename... Args>
1192  size_t HashWithOptions(const Args&... args) const {
1193  return fast_hash_combine(opcode, derived_this().inputs(), args...);
1194  }
1195  size_t hash_value(
1196  HashingStrategy strategy = HashingStrategy::kDefault) const {
1197  return HashWithOptions(derived_this().options());
1198  }
1199 
1200  void PrintInputs(std::ostream& os, const std::string& op_index_prefix) const {
1201  os << "(";
1202  bool first = true;
1203  for (OpIndex input : inputs()) {
1204  if (!first) os << ", ";
1205  first = false;
1206  os << op_index_prefix << input.id();
1207  }
1208  os << ")";
1209  }
1210 
1211  void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const {
1212  const auto& options = derived_this().options();
1213  constexpr size_t options_count =
1214  std::tuple_size<std::remove_reference_t<decltype(options)>>::value;
1215  if (options_count == 0) {
1216  return;
1217  }
1218  PrintOptionsHelper(os, options, std::make_index_sequence<options_count>());
1219  }
1220 
1221  // Check graph invariants for this operation. Will be invoked in debug mode
1222  // immediately upon construction.
1223  // Concrete Operator classes are expected to re-define it.
1224  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {}
1225 
1226  private:
1227  template <class... T, size_t... I>
1228  static void PrintOptionsHelper(std::ostream& os,
1229  const std::tuple<T...>& options,
1230  std::index_sequence<I...>) {
1231  os << "[";
1232  bool first = true;
1233  USE(first);
1234  ((first ? (first = false, os << std::get<I>(options))
1235  : os << ", " << std::get<I>(options)),
1236  ...);
1237  os << "]";
1238  }
1239 
1240  // All Operations have to define the outputs_rep function, to which
1241  // Operation::outputs_rep() will forward, based on their opcode. If you forget
1242  // to define it, then Operation::outputs_rep() would forward to itself,
1243  // resulting in an infinite loop. To avoid this, we define here in OperationT
1244  // a private version outputs_rep (with no implementation): if an operation
1245  // forgets to define outputs_rep, then Operation::outputs_rep() tries to call
1246  // this private version, which fails at compile time.
1247  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const;
1248 
1249  // Returns a vector of the input representations.
1250  // The passed in {storage} can be used to store the underlying data.
1251  // The returned vector might be smaller than the input_count in which case the
1252  // additional inputs are assumed to have no register representation.
1253  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
1254  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const;
1255 };
1256 
1257 template <size_t InputCount, class Derived>
1258 struct FixedArityOperationT : OperationT<Derived> {
1259  // Enable concise base access in derived struct.
1260  using Base = FixedArityOperationT;
1261 
1262  // Shadow Operation::input_count to exploit static knowledge.
1263  static constexpr uint16_t input_count = InputCount;
1264 
1265  template <class... Args>
1266  explicit FixedArityOperationT(Args... args)
1267  : OperationT<Derived>(InputCount) {
1268  static_assert(sizeof...(Args) == InputCount, "wrong number of inputs");
1269  size_t i = 0;
1270  OpIndex* inputs = this->inputs().begin();
1271  ((inputs[i++] = args), ...);
1272  }
1273 
1274  // Redefine the input initialization to tell C++ about the static input size.
1275  template <class... Args>
1276  static Derived& New(Graph* graph, Args... args) {
1277  Derived& result =
1278  OperationT<Derived>::New(graph, InputCount, std::move(args)...);
1279  return result;
1280  }
1281 
1282  template <typename Fn, typename Mapper, size_t... InputI, size_t... OptionI>
1283  V8_INLINE auto ExplodeImpl(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper,
1284  std::index_sequence<InputI...>,
1285  std::index_sequence<OptionI...>) const {
1286  auto options = this->derived_this().options();
1287  USE(options);
1288  return fn(mapper.Map(this->input(InputI))...,
1289  std::get<OptionI>(options)...);
1290  }
1291 
1292  template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
1293  V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
1294  return ExplodeImpl(
1295  fn, mapper, std::make_index_sequence<input_count>(),
1296  std::make_index_sequence<
1297  std::tuple_size_v<decltype(this->derived_this().options())>>());
1298  }
1299 };

1390 // DeadOp is a special operation that can be used by analyzers to mark
1391 // operations as being dead (typically, it should be used by calling the Graph's
1392 // KillOperation method, which will Replace the old operation by a DeadOp).
1393 // CopyingPhase and Analyzers should ignore Dead operations. A Dead operation
1394 // should never be the input of a non-dead operation.
1395 struct DeadOp : FixedArityOperationT<0, DeadOp> {
1396  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
1397 
1398  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
1399 
1400  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
1401  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
1402  return {};
1403  }
1404 
1405  auto options() const { return std::tuple{}; }
1406 };

1543 // Word32SignHint is a type-hint used during Maglev->Turboshaft
1544 // translation to avoid having multiple values being used as both Int32 and
1545 // Uint32: for such cases, Maglev has explicit conversions, and it's helpful to
1546 // also have them in Turboshaft. Eventually, Word32SignHint is just a
1547 // nop in Turboshaft, since as far as Machine level graph is concerned, both
1548 // Int32 and Uint32 are just Word32 registers.
1549 struct Word32SignHintOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, Word32SignHintOp> {
1550  enum class Sign : bool { kSigned, kUnsigned };
1551  Sign sign;
1552 
1553  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
1554  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
1555  return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
1556  }
1557 
1558  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
1559  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
1560  return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
1561  }
1562 
1563  V<Word32> input() const { return Base::input<Word32>(0); }
1564 
1565  Word32SignHintOp(V<Word32> input, Sign sign) : Base(input), sign(sign) {}
1566 
1567  auto options() const { return std::tuple{sign}; }
1568 };

1601  template <class WordType = Word>
1602  V<WordType> left() const
1603  requires(IsWord<WordType>())
1604  {
1605  return input<WordType>(0);
1606  }
1607  template <class WordType = Word>
1608  V<WordType> right() const
1609  requires(IsWord<WordType>())
1610  {
1611  return input<WordType>(1);
1612  }
1613 
1614  bool IsCommutative() const { return IsCommutative(kind); }
1615 
1616  static bool IsCommutative(Kind kind) {
1617  switch (kind) {
1618  case Kind::kAdd:
1619  case Kind::kMul:
1620  case Kind::kSignedMulOverflownBits:
1621  case Kind::kUnsignedMulOverflownBits:
1622  case Kind::kBitwiseAnd:
1623  case Kind::kBitwiseOr:
1624  case Kind::kBitwiseXor:
1625  return true;
1626  case Kind::kSub:
1627  case Kind::kSignedDiv:
1628  case Kind::kUnsignedDiv:
1629  case Kind::kSignedMod:
1630  case Kind::kUnsignedMod:
1631  return false;
1632  }
1633  }
1634 
1635  static bool IsAssociative(Kind kind) {
1636  switch (kind) {
1637  case Kind::kAdd:
1638  case Kind::kMul:
1639  case Kind::kBitwiseAnd:
1640  case Kind::kBitwiseOr:
1641  case Kind::kBitwiseXor:
1642  return true;
1643  case Kind::kSignedMulOverflownBits:
1644  case Kind::kUnsignedMulOverflownBits:
1645  case Kind::kSub:
1646  case Kind::kSignedDiv:
1647  case Kind::kUnsignedDiv:
1648  case Kind::kSignedMod:
1649  case Kind::kUnsignedMod:
1650  return false;
1651  }
1652  }
1653  // The Word32 and Word64 versions of the operator compute the same result when
1654  // truncated to 32 bit.
1655  static bool AllowsWord64ToWord32Truncation(Kind kind) {
1656  switch (kind) {
1657  case Kind::kAdd:
1658  case Kind::kMul:
1659  case Kind::kBitwiseAnd:
1660  case Kind::kBitwiseOr:
1661  case Kind::kBitwiseXor:
1662  case Kind::kSub:
1663  return true;
1664  case Kind::kSignedMulOverflownBits:
1665  case Kind::kUnsignedMulOverflownBits:
1666  case Kind::kSignedDiv:
1667  case Kind::kUnsignedDiv:
1668  case Kind::kSignedMod:
1669  case Kind::kUnsignedMod:
1670  return false;
1671  }
1672  }
1673 
1674  WordBinopOp(V<Word> left, V<Word> right, Kind kind, WordRepresentation rep)
1675  : Base(left, right), kind(kind), rep(rep) {}
1676 
1677  auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind, rep}; }
1678  void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
1679 };

2000 struct ShiftOp : FixedArityOperationT<2, ShiftOp> {
2001  enum class Kind : uint8_t {
2002  kShiftRightArithmeticShiftOutZeros,
2003  kShiftRightArithmetic,
2004  kShiftRightLogical,
2005  kShiftLeft,
2006  kRotateRight,
2007  kRotateLeft
2008  };
2009  Kind kind;
2010  WordRepresentation rep;
2011 
2012  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
2013  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
2014  return base::VectorOf(static_cast<const RegisterRepresentation*>(&rep), 1);
2015  }
2016 
2017  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
2018  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
2019  return InitVectorOf(storage,
2020  {static_cast<const RegisterRepresentation&>(rep),
2021  RegisterRepresentation::Word32()});
2022  }
2023 
2024  template <typename WordT = Word>
2025  requires(IsWord<WordT>())
2026  V<WordT> left() const {
2027  DCHECK(IsValidTypeFor<WordT>(rep));
2028  return input<WordT>(0);
2029  }
2030  V<Word32> right() const { return input<Word32>(1); }
2031 
2032  bool IsRightShift() const { return IsRightShift(kind); }
2033 
2034  static bool IsRightShift(Kind kind) {
2035  switch (kind) {
2036  case Kind::kShiftRightArithmeticShiftOutZeros:
2037  case Kind::kShiftRightArithmetic:
2038  case Kind::kShiftRightLogical:
2039  return true;
2040  case Kind::kShiftLeft:
2041  case Kind::kRotateRight:
2042  case Kind::kRotateLeft:
2043  return false;
2044  }
2045  }
2046  // The Word32 and Word64 versions of the operator compute the same result when
2047  // truncated to 32 bit.
2048  static bool AllowsWord64ToWord32Truncation(Kind kind) {
2049  switch (kind) {
2050  case Kind::kShiftLeft:
2051  return true;
2052  case Kind::kShiftRightArithmeticShiftOutZeros:
2053  case Kind::kShiftRightArithmetic:
2054  case Kind::kShiftRightLogical:
2055  case Kind::kRotateRight:
2056  case Kind::kRotateLeft:
2057  return false;
2058  }
2059  }
2060 
2061  ShiftOp(V<Word> left, V<Word32> right, Kind kind, WordRepresentation rep)
2062  : Base(left, right), kind(kind), rep(rep) {}
2063

2065 };

2069 struct ComparisonOp : FixedArityOperationT<2, ComparisonOp> {
2070  enum class Kind : uint8_t {
2071  kEqual,
2072  kSignedLessThan,
2073  kSignedLessThanOrEqual,
2074  kUnsignedLessThan,
2075  kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual
2076  };
2077  Kind kind;
2078  RegisterRepresentation rep;
2079 
2080  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
2081  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
2082  return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
2083  }
2084 
2085  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
2086  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
2087  return InputsRepFactory::PairOf(rep);
2088  }
2089 
2090  static bool IsCommutative(Kind kind) { return kind == Kind::kEqual; }
2091 
2092  template <typename T = Any>
2093  V<T> left() const {
2094  DCHECK(IsValidTypeFor<T>(rep));
2095  return input<T>(0);
2096  }
2097  template <typename T = Any>
2098  V<T> right() const {
2099  DCHECK(IsValidTypeFor<T>(rep));
2100  return input<T>(1);
2101  }
2102 
2103  ComparisonOp(V<Any> left, V<Any> right, Kind kind, RegisterRepresentation rep)
2104  : Base(left, right), kind(kind), rep(rep) {}
2105 
2106  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
2107  if (kind == Kind::kEqual) {
2108  DCHECK(rep == any_of(RegisterRepresentation::Word32(),
2109  RegisterRepresentation::Word64(),
2110  RegisterRepresentation::Float32(),
2111  RegisterRepresentation::Float64(),
2112  RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()));
2113 
2114  RegisterRepresentation input_rep = rep;
2115 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
2116  // In the presence of pointer compression, we only compare the lower
2117  // 32bit.
2118  if (input_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()) {
2119  input_rep = RegisterRepresentation::Compressed();
2120  }
2121 #endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
2122 #ifdef DEBUG
2123  ValidateOpInputRep(graph, left(), input_rep);
2124  ValidateOpInputRep(graph, right(), input_rep);
2125 #endif // DEBUG
2126  USE(input_rep);
2127  } else {
2128  DCHECK_EQ(rep, any_of(RegisterRepresentation::Word32(),
2129  RegisterRepresentation::Word64(),
2130  RegisterRepresentation::Float32(),
2131  RegisterRepresentation::Float64()));
2132  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
2133  rep == any_of(RegisterRepresentation::Float32(),
2134  RegisterRepresentation::Float64()),
2135  kind == any_of(Kind::kSignedLessThan, Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual));
2136  }
2137  }
2138  auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind, rep}; }
2139 };
2140 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os,
2141  ComparisonOp::Kind kind);
2142 DEFINE_MULTI_SWITCH_INTEGRAL(ComparisonOp::Kind, 8)
2143 
2144 struct ChangeOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, ChangeOp> {
2145  enum class Kind : uint8_t {
2146  // convert between different floating-point types. Note that the
2147  // Float64->Float32 conversion is truncating.
2148  kFloatConversion,
2149  // overflow guaranteed to result in the minimal integer
2150  kSignedFloatTruncateOverflowToMin,
2151  kUnsignedFloatTruncateOverflowToMin,
2152  // JS semantics float64 to word32 truncation
2153  // https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-touint32
2154  kJSFloatTruncate,
2155  // convert float64 to float16, then bitcast word32. Used for storing into
2156  // Float16Array and Math.fround16.
2157  kJSFloat16TruncateWithBitcast,
2158  // bitcast word32 to float16 and convert to float64. Used for loading from
2159  // Float16Array and Math.fround16.
2160  kJSFloat16ChangeWithBitcast,
2161  // convert (un)signed integer to floating-point value
2162  kSignedToFloat,
2163  kUnsignedToFloat,
2164  // extract half of a float64 value
2165  kExtractHighHalf,
2166  kExtractLowHalf,
2167  // increase bit-width for unsigned integer values
2168  kZeroExtend,
2169  // increase bid-width for signed integer values
2170  kSignExtend,
2171  // truncate word64 to word32
2172  kTruncate,
2173  // preserve bits, change meaning
2174  kBitcast
2175  };
2176  // Violated assumptions result in undefined behavior.
2177  enum class Assumption : uint8_t {
2178  kNoAssumption,
2179  // Used for conversions from floating-point to integer, assumes that the
2180  // value doesn't exceed the integer range.
2181  kNoOverflow,
2182  // Assume that the original value can be recovered by a corresponding
2183  // reverse transformation.
2184  kReversible,
2185  };
2186  Kind kind;
2187  // Reversible means undefined behavior if value cannot be represented
2188  // precisely.
2189  Assumption assumption;
2190  RegisterRepresentation from;
2191  RegisterRepresentation to;
2192 
2193  // Returns true if change<kind>(change<reverse_kind>(a)) == a for all a.
2194  // This assumes that change<reverse_kind> uses the inverted {from} and {to}
2195  // representations, i.e. the input to the inner change op has the same
2196  // representation as the result of the outer change op.
2197  static bool IsReversible(Kind kind, Assumption assumption,
2198  RegisterRepresentation from,
2199  RegisterRepresentation to, Kind reverse_kind,
2200  bool signalling_nan_possible) {
2201  switch (kind) {
2202  case Kind::kFloatConversion:
2203  return from == RegisterRepresentation::Float32() &&
2204  to == RegisterRepresentation::Float64() &&
2205  reverse_kind == Kind::kFloatConversion &&
2206  !signalling_nan_possible;
2207  case Kind::kSignedFloatTruncateOverflowToMin:
2208  return assumption == Assumption::kReversible &&
2209  reverse_kind == Kind::kSignedToFloat;
2210  case Kind::kUnsignedFloatTruncateOverflowToMin:
2211  return assumption == Assumption::kReversible &&
2212  reverse_kind == Kind::kUnsignedToFloat;
2213  case Kind::kJSFloatTruncate:
2214  return false;
2215  case Kind::kJSFloat16TruncateWithBitcast:
2216  case Kind::kJSFloat16ChangeWithBitcast:
2217  return false;
2218  case Kind::kSignedToFloat:
2219  if (from == RegisterRepresentation::Word32() &&
2220  to == RegisterRepresentation::Float64()) {
2221  return reverse_kind == any_of(Kind::kSignedFloatTruncateOverflowToMin,
2222  Kind::kJSFloatTruncate);
2223  } else {
2224  return assumption == Assumption::kReversible &&
2225  reverse_kind ==
2226  any_of(Kind::kSignedFloatTruncateOverflowToMin);
2227  }
2228  case Kind::kUnsignedToFloat:
2229  if (from == RegisterRepresentation::Word32() &&
2230  to == RegisterRepresentation::Float64()) {
2231  return reverse_kind ==
2232  any_of(Kind::kUnsignedFloatTruncateOverflowToMin,
2233  Kind::kJSFloatTruncate);
2234  } else {
2235  return assumption == Assumption::kReversible &&
2236  reverse_kind == Kind::kUnsignedFloatTruncateOverflowToMin;
2237  }
2238  case Kind::kExtractHighHalf:
2239  case Kind::kExtractLowHalf:
2240  return false;
2241  case Kind::kZeroExtend:
2242  case Kind::kSignExtend:
2243  DCHECK_EQ(from, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
2244  DCHECK_EQ(to, RegisterRepresentation::Word64());
2245  return reverse_kind == Kind::kTruncate;
2246  case Kind::kTruncate:
2247  DCHECK_EQ(from, RegisterRepresentation::Word64());
2248  DCHECK_EQ(to, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
2249  return reverse_kind == Kind::kBitcast;
2250  case Kind::kBitcast:
2251  return reverse_kind == Kind::kBitcast;
2252  }
2253  }
2254 
2255  bool IsReversibleBy(Kind reverse_kind, bool signalling_nan_possible) const {
2256  return IsReversible(kind, assumption, from, to, reverse_kind,
2257  signalling_nan_possible);
2258  }
2259 
2260  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
2261  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
2262  return base::VectorOf(&to, 1);
2263  }
2264 
2265  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
2266  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
2267  return InputsRepFactory::SingleRep(from);
2268  }
2269 
2270  template <typename Type = Untagged>
2271  requires IsUntagged<Type>
2272  V<Type> input() const {
2273  DCHECK(IsValidTypeFor<Type>(from));
2274  return Base::input<Type>(0);
2275  }
2276 
2277  ChangeOp(V<Untagged> input, Kind kind, Assumption assumption,
2278  RegisterRepresentation from, RegisterRepresentation to)
2279  : Base(input), kind(kind), assumption(assumption), from(from), to(to) {}
2280 
2281  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
2282  DCHECK_NE(from, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
2283  DCHECK_NE(to, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
2284  // Bitcasts from and to Tagged should use a TaggedBitcast instead (which has
2285  // different effects, since it's unsafe to reorder such bitcasts accross
2286  // GCs).
2287  }
2288  auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind, assumption, from, to}; }
2289 };
2290 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os,
2291  ChangeOp::Kind kind);
2292 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os,
2293  ChangeOp::Assumption assumption);
2294 DEFINE_MULTI_SWITCH_INTEGRAL(ChangeOp::Kind, 16)
2295 DEFINE_MULTI_SWITCH_INTEGRAL(ChangeOp::Assumption, 4)
2296 
2297 struct ChangeOrDeoptOp : FixedArityOperationT<2, ChangeOrDeoptOp> {
2298  enum class Kind : uint8_t {
2299  kUint32ToInt32,
2300  kInt64ToInt32,
2301  kInt64ToAdditiveSafeInteger,
2302  kUint64ToInt32,
2303  kUint64ToInt64,
2304  kFloat64ToInt32,
2305  kFloat64ToUint32,
2306  kFloat64ToAdditiveSafeInteger,
2307  kFloat64ToInt64,
2308  kFloat64NotHole,
2309  };
2310  Kind kind;
2311  CheckForMinusZeroMode minus_zero_mode;
2312  FeedbackSource feedback;
2313 
2314  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanDeopt();
2315  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
2316  switch (kind) {
2317  case Kind::kUint32ToInt32:
2318  case Kind::kInt64ToInt32:
2319  case Kind::kUint64ToInt32:
2320  case Kind::kFloat64ToInt32:
2321  case Kind::kFloat64ToUint32:
2322  return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
2323  case Kind::kUint64ToInt64:
2324  case Kind::kInt64ToAdditiveSafeInteger:
2325  case Kind::kFloat64ToAdditiveSafeInteger:

2327  return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Word64()>();
2328  case Kind::kFloat64NotHole:
2329  return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Float64()>();
2330  }
2331  }
2332 
2333  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
2334  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
2335  switch (kind) {
2336  case Kind::kUint32ToInt32:
2337  return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
2338  case Kind::kInt64ToInt32:
2339  case Kind::kInt64ToAdditiveSafeInteger:
2340  case Kind::kUint64ToInt32:
2341  case Kind::kUint64ToInt64:
2342  return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word64()>();
2343  case Kind::kFloat64ToInt32:
2344  case Kind::kFloat64ToUint32:
2345  case Kind::kFloat64ToAdditiveSafeInteger:
2346  case Kind::kFloat64ToInt64:
2347  case Kind::kFloat64NotHole:
2348  return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Float64()>();
2349  }
2350  }
2351 
2352  V<Untagged> input() const { return Base::input<Untagged>(0); }
2353  V<FrameState> frame_state() const { return Base::input<FrameState>(1); }
2354 
2355  ChangeOrDeoptOp(V<Untagged> input, V<FrameState> frame_state, Kind kind,
2356  CheckForMinusZeroMode minus_zero_mode,
2357  const FeedbackSource& feedback)
2358  : Base(input, frame_state),
2359  kind(kind),
2360  minus_zero_mode(minus_zero_mode),
2361  feedback(feedback) {}
2362 
2363  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
2364  DCHECK(Get(graph, frame_state()).Is<FrameStateOp>());
2365  }
2366 
2367  auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind, minus_zero_mode, feedback}; }
2368 };

2370  ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind kind);

2372 // Perform a conversion and return a pair of the result and a bit if it was
2373 // successful.
2374 struct TryChangeOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, TryChangeOp> {
2375  static constexpr uint32_t kSuccessValue = 1;
2376  static constexpr uint32_t kFailureValue = 0;
2377  enum class Kind : uint8_t {
2378  // The result of the truncation is undefined if the result is out of range.
2379  kSignedFloatTruncateOverflowUndefined,
2380  kUnsignedFloatTruncateOverflowUndefined,
2381  };
2382  Kind kind;
2383  FloatRepresentation from;
2384  WordRepresentation to;
2385 
2386  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
2387  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
2388  switch (to.value()) {
2389  case WordRepresentation::Word32():
2390  return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Word32(),
2391  RegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
2392  case WordRepresentation::Word64():
2393  return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Word64(),
2394  RegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
2395  }
2396  }
2397

2399  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
2400  return InputsRepFactory::SingleRep(from);
2401  }
2402 
2403  V<Float> input() const { return Base::input<Float>(0); }
2404

2406  WordRepresentation to)
2407  : Base(input), kind(kind), from(from), to(to) {}
2408

2410 };

2412  TryChangeOp::Kind kind);

2436 struct TaggedBitcastOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, TaggedBitcastOp> {
2437  enum class Kind : uint8_t {
2438  kSmi, // This is a bitcast from a Word to a Smi or from a Smi to a Word
2439  kHeapObject, // This is a bitcast from or to a Heap Object
2440  kTagAndSmiBits, // This is a bitcast where only access to the tag and the
2441  // smi bits (if it's a smi) are valid
2442  kAny
2443  };
2444  Kind kind;
2445  RegisterRepresentation from;
2446  RegisterRepresentation to;
2447 
2448  OpEffects Effects() const {
2449  switch (kind) {
2450  case Kind::kSmi:
2451  case Kind::kTagAndSmiBits:
2452  return OpEffects();
2453  case Kind::kHeapObject:
2454  case Kind::kAny:
2455  // Due to moving GC, converting from or to pointers doesn't commute with
2456  // GC.
2457  return OpEffects().CanDoRawHeapAccess();
2458  }
2459  }
2460 
2461  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
2462  return base::VectorOf(&to, 1);
2463  }
2464 
2465  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
2466  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
2467  return InputsRepFactory::SingleRep(from);
2468  }
2469 
2470  OpIndex input() const { return Base::input(0); }
2471 
2472  TaggedBitcastOp(OpIndex input, RegisterRepresentation from,
2473  RegisterRepresentation to, Kind kind)
2474  : Base(input), kind(kind), from(from), to(to) {}
2475 
2476  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
2477  if (kind == Kind::kSmi) {
2478  DCHECK((from.IsWord() && to.IsTaggedOrCompressed()) ||
2479  (from.IsTaggedOrCompressed() && to.IsWord()));
2480  DCHECK_IMPLIES(from == RegisterRepresentation::Word64() ||
2481  to == RegisterRepresentation::Word64(),
2482  Is64());
2483  } else {
2484  // TODO(nicohartmann@): Without implicit truncation, the first case might
2485  // not be correct anymore.
2486  DCHECK((from.IsWord() && to == RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()) ||
2487  (from == RegisterRepresentation::Tagged() &&
2488  to == RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr()) ||
2489  (from == RegisterRepresentation::Compressed() &&
2490  to == RegisterRepresentation::Word32()));
2491  }
2492  }
2493  auto options() const { return std::tuple{from, to, kind}; }
2494 };
2495 std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, TaggedBitcastOp::Kind assumption);

2539 struct PhiOp : OperationT<PhiOp> {
2540  RegisterRepresentation rep;
2541 
2542  // Phis have to remain at the beginning of the current block. As effects
2543  // cannot express this completely, we just mark them as having no effects but
2544  // treat them specially when scheduling operations.
2545  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
2546  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
2547  return base::VectorOf(&rep, 1);
2548  }
2549 
2550  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
2551  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
2552  storage.resize(input_count);
2553  for (size_t i = 0; i < input_count; ++i) {
2554  storage[i] = rep;
2555  }
2556  return base::VectorOf(storage);
2557  }
2558 
2559  static constexpr size_t kLoopPhiBackEdgeIndex = 1;
2560 
2561  explicit PhiOp(base::Vector<const OpIndex> inputs, RegisterRepresentation rep)
2562  : Base(inputs), rep(rep) {}
2563 
2564  template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
2565  V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
2566  auto mapped_inputs = mapper.template Map<64>(inputs());
2567  return fn(base::VectorOf(mapped_inputs), rep);
2568  }
2569 
2570  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const { DCHECK_GT(input_count, 0); }
2571  auto options() const { return std::tuple{rep}; }
2572 };

2597 struct ConstantOp : FixedArityOperationT<0, ConstantOp> {
2598  enum class Kind : uint8_t {
2599  kWord32,
2600  kWord64,
2601  kFloat32,
2602  kFloat64,
2603  kSmi,
2604  kNumber, // TODO(tebbi): See if we can avoid number constants.
2605  kTaggedIndex,
2606  kExternal,
2607  kHeapObject,
2608  kCompressedHeapObject,
2609  kTrustedHeapObject,
2610  kRelocatableWasmCall,
2611  kRelocatableWasmStubCall,
2612  kRelocatableWasmIndirectCallTarget,
2613  kRelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId
2614  };
2615 
2616  Kind kind;
2617  RegisterRepresentation rep = Representation(kind);
2618  union Storage {
2619  uint64_t integral;
2620  i::Float32 float32;
2621  i::Float64 float64;
2622  ExternalReference external;
2623  IndirectHandle<HeapObject> handle;
2624 
2625  Storage(uint64_t integral = 0) : integral(integral) {}
2626  Storage(i::Tagged<Smi> smi) : integral(smi.ptr()) {}
2627  Storage(i::Float64 constant) : float64(constant) {}
2628  Storage(i::Float32 constant) : float32(constant) {}
2629  Storage(ExternalReference constant) : external(constant) {}
2630  Storage(IndirectHandle<HeapObject> constant) : handle(constant) {}
2631 
2632  inline bool operator==(const ConstantOp::Storage&) const {
2633  // It is tricky to implement this properly. We currently need to define
2634  // this for the matchers, but this should never be called.
2635  UNREACHABLE();
2636  }
2637  } storage;
2638 
2639  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
2640  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
2641  return base::VectorOf(&rep, 1);
2642  }
2643 
2644  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
2645  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>&) const {
2646  return {};
2647  }
2648 
2649  static RegisterRepresentation Representation(Kind kind) {
2650  switch (kind) {
2651  case Kind::kRelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId:
2652  case Kind::kWord32:
2653  return RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
2654  case Kind::kWord64:
2655  return RegisterRepresentation::Word64();
2656  case Kind::kFloat32:
2657  return RegisterRepresentation::Float32();
2658  case Kind::kFloat64:
2659  return RegisterRepresentation::Float64();
2660  case Kind::kExternal:
2661  case Kind::kTaggedIndex:
2662  case Kind::kTrustedHeapObject:
2663  case Kind::kRelocatableWasmCall:
2664  case Kind::kRelocatableWasmStubCall:
2665  return RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr();
2666  case Kind::kRelocatableWasmIndirectCallTarget:
2667  return RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
2668  case Kind::kSmi:
2669  case Kind::kHeapObject:
2670  case Kind::kNumber:
2671  return RegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
2672  case Kind::kCompressedHeapObject:
2673  return RegisterRepresentation::Compressed();
2674  }
2675  }
2676 
2677  ConstantOp(Kind kind, Storage storage)
2678  : Base(), kind(kind), storage(storage) {}
2679 
2680  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
2681  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
2682  kind == Kind::kWord32,
2683  storage.integral <= WordRepresentation::Word32().MaxUnsignedValue());
2684  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
2685  kind == Kind::kRelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId,
2686  storage.integral <= WordRepresentation::Word32().MaxSignedValue());
2687  }
2688 
2689  uint64_t integral() const {
2690  DCHECK(IsIntegral());
2691  return storage.integral;
2692  }
2693 
2694  int64_t signed_integral() const {
2695  DCHECK(IsIntegral());
2696  switch (kind) {
2697  case Kind::kWord32:
2698  case Kind::kRelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId:
2699  return static_cast<int32_t>(storage.integral);
2700  case Kind::kWord64:
2701  return static_cast<int64_t>(storage.integral);
2702  default:
2703  UNREACHABLE();
2704  }
2705  }
2706 
2707  uint32_t word32() const {
2708  DCHECK(kind == Kind::kWord32 || kind == Kind::kWord64);
2709  return static_cast<uint32_t>(storage.integral);
2710  }
2711 
2712  uint64_t word64() const {
2713  DCHECK_EQ(kind, Kind::kWord64);
2714  return static_cast<uint64_t>(storage.integral);
2715  }
2716 
2717  i::Tagged<Smi> smi() const {
2718  DCHECK_EQ(kind, Kind::kSmi);
2719  return i::Tagged<Smi>(storage.integral);
2720  }
2721 
2722  i::Float64 number() const {
2723  DCHECK_EQ(kind, Kind::kNumber);
2724  return storage.float64;
2725  }
2726 
2727  i::Float32 float32() const {
2728  DCHECK_EQ(kind, Kind::kFloat32);
2729  return storage.float32;
2730  }
2731 
2732  i::Float64 float64() const {
2733  DCHECK_EQ(kind, Kind::kFloat64);
2734  return storage.float64;
2735  }
2736 
2737  int32_t tagged_index() const {
2738  DCHECK_EQ(kind, Kind::kTaggedIndex);
2739  return static_cast<int32_t>(static_cast<uint32_t>(storage.integral));
2740  }
2741 
2742  ExternalReference external_reference() const {
2743  DCHECK_EQ(kind, Kind::kExternal);
2744  return storage.external;
2745  }
2746 
2747  IndirectHandle<i::HeapObject> handle() const {
2748  DCHECK(kind == Kind::kHeapObject || kind == Kind::kCompressedHeapObject ||
2749  kind == Kind::kTrustedHeapObject);
2750  return storage.handle;
2751  }
2752 
2753  bool IsWord(uint64_t value) const {
2754  switch (kind) {
2755  case Kind::kWord32:
2756  return static_cast<uint32_t>(value) == word32();
2757  case Kind::kWord64:
2758  return value == word64();
2759  default:
2760  UNREACHABLE();
2761  }
2762  }
2763 
2764  bool IsIntegral() const {
2765  return kind == Kind::kWord32 || kind == Kind::kWord64 ||
2766  kind == Kind::kRelocatableWasmCall ||
2767  kind == Kind::kRelocatableWasmStubCall ||
2768  kind == Kind::kRelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId ||
2769  kind == Kind::kRelocatableWasmIndirectCallTarget;
2770  }
2771 
2772  auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind, storage}; }
2773 
2774  void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
2775  size_t hash_value(
2776  HashingStrategy strategy = HashingStrategy::kDefault) const {
2777  switch (kind) {
2778  case Kind::kWord32:
2779  case Kind::kWord64:
2780  case Kind::kSmi:
2781  case Kind::kTaggedIndex:
2782  case Kind::kRelocatableWasmCall:
2783  case Kind::kRelocatableWasmStubCall:
2784  case Kind::kRelocatableWasmIndirectCallTarget:
2785  case Kind::kRelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId:
2786  return HashWithOptions(storage.integral);
2787  case Kind::kFloat32:
2788  return HashWithOptions(storage.float32.get_bits());
2789  case Kind::kFloat64:
2790  case Kind::kNumber:
2791  return HashWithOptions(storage.float64.get_bits());
2792  case Kind::kExternal:
2793  return HashWithOptions(strategy == HashingStrategy::kMakeSnapshotStable
2794  ? 0
2795  : storage.external.raw());
2796  case Kind::kHeapObject:
2797  case Kind::kCompressedHeapObject:
2798  case Kind::kTrustedHeapObject:
2799  if (strategy == HashingStrategy::kMakeSnapshotStable) {
2800  return HashWithOptions();
2801  }
2802  return HashWithOptions(storage.handle.address());
2803  }
2804  }
2805  bool operator==(const ConstantOp& other) const {
2806  if (kind != other.kind) return false;
2807  switch (kind) {
2808  case Kind::kWord32:
2809  case Kind::kWord64:
2810  case Kind::kSmi:
2811  case Kind::kTaggedIndex:
2812  case Kind::kRelocatableWasmCall:
2813  case Kind::kRelocatableWasmStubCall:
2814  case Kind::kRelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId:
2815  case Kind::kRelocatableWasmIndirectCallTarget:
2816  return storage.integral == other.storage.integral;
2817  case Kind::kFloat32:
2818  // Using a bit_cast to uint32_t in order to return false when comparing
2819  // +0 and -0.
2820  // Note: for JavaScript, it would be fine to return true when both
2821  // values are NaNs, but for Wasm we must not merge NaNs that way.
2822  // Since we canonicalize NaNs for JS anyway, we don't need to treat
2823  // them specially here.
2824  return base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(storage.float32) ==
2825  base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(other.storage.float32);
2826  case Kind::kFloat64:
2827  case Kind::kNumber:
2828  // Using a bit_cast to uint64_t in order to return false when comparing
2829  // +0 and -0.
2830  // Note: for JavaScript, it would be fine to return true when both
2831  // values are NaNs, but for Wasm we must not merge NaNs that way.
2832  // Since we canonicalize NaNs for JS anyway, we don't need to treat
2833  // them specially here.
2834  return base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(storage.float64) ==
2835  base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(other.storage.float64);
2836  case Kind::kExternal:
2837  return storage.external.raw() == other.storage.external.raw();
2838  case Kind::kHeapObject:
2839  case Kind::kCompressedHeapObject:
2840  case Kind::kTrustedHeapObject:
2841  return storage.handle.address() == other.storage.handle.address();
2842  }
2843  }
2844 };
2845 
2846 // Load `loaded_rep` from: base + offset + index * 2^element_size_log2.
2847 // For Kind::tagged_base: subtract kHeapObjectTag,
2848 // `base` has to be the object start.
2849 // For (u)int8/16, the value will be sign- or zero-extended to Word32.
2850 // When result_rep is RegisterRepresentation::Compressed(), then the load does
2851 // not decompress the value.
2852 struct LoadOp : OperationT<LoadOp> {
2853  struct Kind {
2854  // The `base` input is a tagged pointer to a HeapObject.
2855  bool tagged_base : 1;
2856  // The effective address might be unaligned. This is only set to true if
2857  // the platform does not support unaligned loads for the given
2858  // MemoryRepresentation natively.
2859  bool maybe_unaligned : 1;
2860  // There is a Wasm trap handler for out-of-bounds accesses.
2861  bool with_trap_handler : 1;
2862  // The wasm trap handler is used for null accesses. Note that this requires
2863  // with_trap_handler as well.
2864  bool trap_on_null : 1;
2865  // If {load_eliminable} is true, then:
2866  // - Stores/Loads at this address cannot overlap. Concretely, it means
2867  // that something like this cannot happen:
2868  //
2869  // const u32s = Uint32Array.of(3, 8);
2870  // const u8s = new Uint8Array(u32s.buffer);
2871  // u32s[0] = 0xffffffff;
2872  // u8s[1] = 0; // Overlaps with previous store!
2873  //
2874  // - Stores/Loads at this address have a canonical base. Concretely, it
2875  // means that something like this cannot happen:
2876  //
2877  // let buffer = new ArrayBuffer(10000);
2878  // let ta1 = new Int32Array(buffer, 0/*offset*/);
2879  // let ta2 = new Int32Array(buffer, 100*4/*offset*/);
2880  // ta2[0] = 0xff;
2881  // ta1[100] = 42; // Same destination as the previous store!
2882  //
2883  // - No other thread can modify the underlying value. E.g. in the case of
2884  // loading the wasm stack limit, other threads can modify the loaded
2885  // value, so we always have to reload it.
2886  //
2887  // This is mainly used for load elimination: when stores/loads don't have
2888  // the {load_eliminable} bit set to true, more things need to be
2889  // invalidated.
2890  // In the main JS pipeline, only ArrayBuffers (= TypedArray/DataView)
2891  // loads/stores have this {load_eliminable} set to false,
2892  // and all other loads have it to true.
2893  bool load_eliminable : 1;
2894  // The loaded value may not change.
2895  bool is_immutable : 1;
2896  // The load should be atomic.
2897  bool is_atomic : 1;
2898 
2899  static constexpr Kind Aligned(BaseTaggedness base_is_tagged) {
2900  switch (base_is_tagged) {
2901  case BaseTaggedness::kTaggedBase:
2902  return TaggedBase();
2903  case BaseTaggedness::kUntaggedBase:
2904  return RawAligned();
2905  }
2906  }
2907  static constexpr Kind TaggedBase() {
2908  return {.tagged_base = true,
2909  .maybe_unaligned = false,
2910  .with_trap_handler = false,
2911  .trap_on_null = false,
2912  .load_eliminable = true,
2913  .is_immutable = false,
2914  .is_atomic = false};
2915  }
2916  static constexpr Kind RawAligned() {
2917  return {.tagged_base = false,
2918  .maybe_unaligned = false,
2919  .with_trap_handler = false,
2920  .trap_on_null = false,
2921  .load_eliminable = true,
2922  .is_immutable = false,
2923  .is_atomic = false};
2924  }
2925  static constexpr Kind RawUnaligned() {
2926  return {.tagged_base = false,
2927  .maybe_unaligned = true,
2928  .with_trap_handler = false,
2929  .trap_on_null = false,
2930  .load_eliminable = true,
2931  .is_immutable = false,
2932  .is_atomic = false};
2933  }
2934  static constexpr Kind Protected() {
2935  return {.tagged_base = false,
2936  .maybe_unaligned = false,
2937  .with_trap_handler = true,
2938  .trap_on_null = false,
2939  .load_eliminable = true,
2940  .is_immutable = false,
2941  .is_atomic = false};
2942  }
2943  static constexpr Kind TrapOnNull() {
2944  return {.tagged_base = true,
2945  .maybe_unaligned = false,
2946  .with_trap_handler = true,
2947  .trap_on_null = true,
2948  .load_eliminable = true,
2949  .is_immutable = false,
2950  .is_atomic = false};
2951  }
2952  static constexpr Kind MaybeUnaligned(MemoryRepresentation rep) {
2953  return rep == MemoryRepresentation::Int8() ||
2954  rep == MemoryRepresentation::Uint8() ||
2955  SupportedOperations::IsUnalignedLoadSupported(rep)
2956  ? LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned()
2957  : LoadOp::Kind::RawUnaligned();
2958  }
2959 
2960  constexpr Kind NotLoadEliminable() {
2961  Kind new_kind = *this;
2962  new_kind.load_eliminable = false;
2963  return new_kind;
2964  }
2965 
2966  constexpr Kind Immutable() const {
2967  Kind new_kind(*this);
2968  new_kind.is_immutable = true;
2969  return new_kind;
2970  }
2971 
2972  constexpr Kind Atomic() const {
2973  Kind new_kind(*this);
2974  new_kind.is_atomic = true;
2975  return new_kind;
2976  }
2977 
2978  bool operator==(const Kind& other) const {
2979  return tagged_base == other.tagged_base &&
2980  maybe_unaligned == other.maybe_unaligned &&
2981  with_trap_handler == other.with_trap_handler &&
2982  load_eliminable == other.load_eliminable &&
2983  is_immutable == other.is_immutable &&
2984  is_atomic == other.is_atomic && trap_on_null == other.trap_on_null;
2985  }
2986  };
2987  Kind kind;
2988  MemoryRepresentation loaded_rep;
2989  RegisterRepresentation result_rep;
2990  uint8_t element_size_log2; // multiply index with 2^element_size_log2
2991  int32_t offset; // add offset to scaled index
2992 
2993  OpEffects Effects() const {
2994  // Loads might depend on checks for pointer validity, object layout, bounds
2995  // checks, etc.
2996  // TODO(tebbi): Distinguish between on-heap and off-heap loads.
2997  OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanReadMemory().CanDependOnChecks();
2998  if (kind.with_trap_handler) effects = effects.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
2999  if (kind.is_atomic) {
3000  // Atomic load should not be reordered with other loads.
3001  effects = effects.CanWriteMemory();
3002  }
3003  return effects;
3004  }
3005  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
3006  return base::VectorOf(&result_rep, 1);
3007  }
3008 
3009  MachineType machine_type() const;
3010 
3011  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
3012  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
3013  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> result =
3014  kind.tagged_base
3015  ? MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
3016  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::WordPtr()>()
3017  : MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(),
3018  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::WordPtr()>();
3019  return index().valid() ? result : base::VectorOf(result.data(), 1);
3020  }
3021 
3022  OpIndex base() const { return input(0); }
3023  OptionalOpIndex index() const {
3024  return input_count == 2 ? input(1) : OpIndex::Invalid();
3025  }
3026 
3027  static constexpr bool OffsetIsValid(int32_t offset, bool tagged_base) {
3028  if (tagged_base) {
3029  // When a Load has the tagged_base Kind, it means that {offset} will
3030  // eventually need a "-kHeapObjectTag". If the {offset} is
3031  // min_int, then subtracting kHeapObjectTag will underflow.
3032  return offset >= std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min() + kHeapObjectTag;
3033  }
3034  return true;
3035  }
3036 
3037  LoadOp(OpIndex base, OptionalOpIndex index, Kind kind,
3038  MemoryRepresentation loaded_rep, RegisterRepresentation result_rep,
3039  int32_t offset, uint8_t element_size_log2)
3040  : Base(1 + index.valid()),
3041  kind(kind),
3042  loaded_rep(loaded_rep),
3043  result_rep(result_rep),
3044  element_size_log2(element_size_log2),
3045  offset(offset) {
3046  input(0) = base;
3047  if (index.valid()) {
3048  input(1) = index.value();
3049  }
3050  }

3052  template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
3053  V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
3054  return fn(mapper.Map(base()), mapper.Map(index()), kind, loaded_rep,
3055  result_rep, offset, element_size_log2);

3058  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
3059  DCHECK(loaded_rep.ToRegisterRepresentation() == result_rep ||
3060  (loaded_rep.IsCompressibleTagged() &&
3061  result_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Compressed()) ||
3062  kind.is_atomic);
3063  DCHECK_IMPLIES(element_size_log2 > 0, index().valid());
3064  DCHECK_IMPLIES(kind.maybe_unaligned,
3065  !SupportedOperations::IsUnalignedLoadSupported(loaded_rep));
3066  DCHECK(OffsetIsValid(offset, kind.tagged_base));
3067  }
3068  static LoadOp& New(Graph* graph, OpIndex base, OptionalOpIndex index,
3069  Kind kind, MemoryRepresentation loaded_rep,
3070  RegisterRepresentation result_rep, int32_t offset,
3071  uint8_t element_size_log2) {
3072  return Base::New(graph, 1 + index.valid(), base, index, kind, loaded_rep,
3073  result_rep, offset, element_size_log2);
3074  }

3079  }
3080 };

3082 V8_INLINE size_t hash_value(LoadOp::Kind kind) {
3083  return base::hash_value(
3084  static_cast<int>(kind.tagged_base) | (kind.maybe_unaligned << 1) |
3085  (kind.load_eliminable << 2) | (kind.is_immutable << 3) |
3086  (kind.with_trap_handler << 4) | (kind.is_atomic << 5));
3087 }
