3185 struct AtomicWord32PairOp : OperationT<AtomicWord32PairOp> {
3186  enum class Kind : uint8_t {
3187  kAdd,
3188  kSub,
3189  kAnd,
3190  kOr,
3191  kXor,
3192  kExchange,
3193  kCompareExchange,
3194  kLoad,
3195  kStore
3196  };
3197 
3198  Kind kind;
3199  int32_t offset;
3200 
3201  static Kind KindFromBinOp(AtomicRMWOp::BinOp bin_op) {
3202  switch (bin_op) {
3203  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kAdd:
3204  return Kind::kAdd;
3205  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kSub:
3206  return Kind::kSub;
3207  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kAnd:
3208  return Kind::kAnd;
3209  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kOr:
3210  return Kind::kOr;
3211  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kXor:
3212  return Kind::kXor;
3213  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kExchange:
3214  return Kind::kExchange;
3215  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kCompareExchange:
3216  return Kind::kCompareExchange;
3217  }
3218  }
3219 
3220  OpEffects Effects() const {
3221  OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanDependOnChecks();
3222  if (kind == Kind::kStore) {
3223  return effects.CanWriteMemory();
3224  }
3225  // Atomic loads are marked as "can write memory" as they should not be
3226  // reordered with other loads. Secondly, they may not be removed even if
3227  // unused as they might make writes of other threads visible.
3228  return effects.CanReadMemory().CanWriteMemory();
3229  }
3230 
3231  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
3232  if (kind == Kind::kStore) return {};
3233  return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Word32(),
3234  RegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
3235  }
3236  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
3237  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
3238  storage.resize(input_count);
3239 
3240  const bool has_index = HasIndex();
3241  storage[0] = RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(); // base
3242  if (has_index) {
3243  storage[1] = RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(); // index
3244  }
3245  if (kind != Kind::kLoad) {
3246  storage[1 + has_index] = RegisterRepresentation::Word32(); // value_low
3247  storage[2 + has_index] = RegisterRepresentation::Word32(); // value_high
3248  if (kind == Kind::kCompareExchange) {
3249  storage[3 + has_index] =
3250  RegisterRepresentation::Word32(); // expected_low
3251  storage[4 + has_index] =
3252  RegisterRepresentation::Word32(); // expected_high
3253  }
3254  }
3255  return base::VectorOf(storage);
3256  }
3257 
3258  V<WordPtr> base() const { return input<WordPtr>(0); }
3259  OptionalV<WordPtr> index() const {
3260  return HasIndex() ? input<WordPtr>(1) : V<WordPtr>::Invalid();
3261  }
3262  OptionalV<Word32> value_low() const {
3263  return kind != Kind::kLoad ? input<Word32>(1 + HasIndex())
3264  : V<Word32>::Invalid();
3265  }
3266  OptionalV<Word32> value_high() const {
3267  return kind != Kind::kLoad ? input<Word32>(2 + HasIndex())
3268  : V<Word32>::Invalid();
3269  }
3270  OptionalV<Word32> expected_low() const {
3271  return kind == Kind::kCompareExchange ? input<Word32>(3 + HasIndex())
3272  : V<Word32>::Invalid();
3273  }
3274  OptionalV<Word32> expected_high() const {
3275  return kind == Kind::kCompareExchange ? input<Word32>(4 + HasIndex())
3276  : V<Word32>::Invalid();
3277  }
3278 
3279 
3280  AtomicWord32PairOp(V<WordPtr> base, OptionalV<WordPtr> index,
3281  OptionalV<Word32> value_low, OptionalV<Word32> value_high,
3282  OptionalV<Word32> expected_low,
3283  OptionalV<Word32> expected_high, Kind kind, int32_t offset)
3284  : Base(InputCount(kind, index.has_value())), kind(kind), offset(offset) {
3285  DCHECK_EQ(value_low.valid(), value_high.valid());
3286  DCHECK_EQ(expected_low.valid(), expected_high.valid());
3287  DCHECK_EQ(kind == Kind::kCompareExchange, expected_low.valid());
3288  DCHECK_EQ(kind != Kind::kLoad, value_low.valid());
3289 
3290  const bool has_index = index.has_value();
3291  DCHECK_EQ(has_index, HasIndex());
3292 
3293  input(0) = base;
3294  if (has_index) input(1) = index.value();
3295  if (kind != Kind::kLoad) {
3296  input(1 + has_index) = value_low.value();
3297  input(2 + has_index) = value_high.value();
3298  if (kind == Kind::kCompareExchange) {
3299  input(3 + has_index) = expected_low.value();
3300  input(4 + has_index) = expected_high.value();
3301  }
3302  }
3303  }
3304 
3305  template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
3306  V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
3307  return fn(mapper.Map(base()), mapper.Map(index()), mapper.Map(value_low()),
3308  mapper.Map(value_high()), mapper.Map(expected_low()),
3309  mapper.Map(expected_high()), kind, offset);
3310  }
3311 
3312  static constexpr size_t InputCount(Kind kind, bool has_index) {
3313  switch (kind) {
3314  case Kind::kLoad:
3315  return 1 + has_index; // base, index?
3316  case Kind::kAdd:
3317  case Kind::kSub:
3318  case Kind::kAnd:
3319  case Kind::kOr:
3320  case Kind::kXor:
3321  case Kind::kExchange:
3322  case Kind::kStore:
3323  return 3 + has_index; // base, index?, value_low, value_high
3324  case Kind::kCompareExchange:
3325  return 5 + has_index; // base, index?, value_low, value_high,
3326  // expected_low, expected_high
3327  }
3328  }
3329  bool HasIndex() const { return input_count == InputCount(kind, true); }
3330 
3331  static AtomicWord32PairOp& New(Graph* graph, V<WordPtr> base,
3332  OptionalV<WordPtr> index,
3333  OptionalV<Word32> value_low,
3334  OptionalV<Word32> value_high,
3335  OptionalV<Word32> expected_low,
3336  OptionalV<Word32> expected_high, Kind kind,
3337  int32_t offset) {
3338  return Base::New(graph, InputCount(kind, index.has_value()), base, index,
3339  value_low, value_high, expected_low, expected_high, kind,
3340  offset);
3341  }

3374 // Store `value` to: base + offset + index * 2^element_size_log2.
3375 // For Kind::tagged_base: subtract kHeapObjectTag,
3376 // `base` has to be the object start.
3377 struct StoreOp : OperationT<StoreOp> {
3378  using Kind = LoadOp::Kind;
3379  Kind kind;
3380  MemoryRepresentation stored_rep;
3381  WriteBarrierKind write_barrier;
3382  uint8_t element_size_log2; // multiply index with 2^element_size_log2
3383  int32_t offset; // add offset to scaled index
3384  bool maybe_initializing_or_transitioning;
3385  uint16_t
3386  shifted_indirect_pointer_tag; // for indirect pointer stores, the
3387  // IndirectPointerTag of the store shifted
3388  // to the right by kIndirectPointerTagShift
3389  // (so it fits into 16 bits).
3390  // TODO(saelo): now that we have a pointer tag in these low-level operations,
3391  // we could also consider passing the external pointer tag (for external
3392  // pointers) through to the macro assembler (where we have routines to work
3393  // with external pointers) instead of handling those earlier in the compiler.
3394  // We might lose the ability to hardcode the table address though.
3395 
3396  OpEffects Effects() const {
3397  // Stores might depend on checks for pointer validity, object layout, bounds
3398  // checks, etc.
3399  // TODO(tebbi): Distinghish between on-heap and off-heap stores.
3400  OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanWriteMemory().CanDependOnChecks();
3401  if (kind.with_trap_handler) effects = effects.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
3402  if (maybe_initializing_or_transitioning) {
3403  effects = effects.CanDoRawHeapAccess();
3404  }
3405  if (kind.is_atomic) {
3406  // Atomic stores should not be eliminated away, even if the situation
3407  // seems to allow e.g. store-store elimination. Elimination is avoided by
3408  // setting the `CanReadMemory` effect.
3409  effects = effects.CanReadMemory();
3410  }
3411  return effects;
3412  }
3413  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
3414 
3415  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
3416  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
3417  RegisterRepresentation base = kind.tagged_base
3418  ? RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()
3419  : RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr();
3420  if (index() == OpIndex::Invalid()) {
3421  return InitVectorOf(
3422  storage, {base, stored_rep.ToRegisterRepresentationForStore()});
3423  }
3424  return InitVectorOf(storage,
3425  {base, stored_rep.ToRegisterRepresentationForStore(),
3426  RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr()});
3427  }
3428 
3429  OpIndex base() const { return input(0); }
3430  OpIndex value() const { return input(1); }
3431  OptionalOpIndex index() const {
3432  return input_count == 3 ? input(2) : OpIndex::Invalid();
3433  }
3434 
3435  IndirectPointerTag indirect_pointer_tag() const {
3436  uint64_t shifted = shifted_indirect_pointer_tag;
3437  return static_cast<IndirectPointerTag>(shifted << kIndirectPointerTagShift);
3438  }
3439 
3440  StoreOp(
3441  OpIndex base, OptionalOpIndex index, OpIndex value, Kind kind,
3442  MemoryRepresentation stored_rep, WriteBarrierKind write_barrier,
3443  int32_t offset, uint8_t element_size_log2,
3444  bool maybe_initializing_or_transitioning,
3445  IndirectPointerTag maybe_indirect_pointer_tag = kIndirectPointerNullTag)
3446  : Base(2 + index.valid()),
3447  kind(kind),
3448  stored_rep(stored_rep),
3449  write_barrier(write_barrier),
3450  element_size_log2(element_size_log2),
3451  offset(offset),
3452  maybe_initializing_or_transitioning(
3453  maybe_initializing_or_transitioning),
3454  shifted_indirect_pointer_tag(maybe_indirect_pointer_tag >>
3455  kIndirectPointerTagShift) {
3456  DCHECK_EQ(indirect_pointer_tag(), maybe_indirect_pointer_tag);
3457  input(0) = base;
3458  input(1) = value;
3459  if (index.valid()) {
3460  input(2) = index.value();
3461  }
3462  }
3463 
3464  template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
3465  V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
3466  return fn(mapper.Map(base()), mapper.Map(index()), mapper.Map(value()),
3467  kind, stored_rep, write_barrier, offset, element_size_log2,
3468  maybe_initializing_or_transitioning, indirect_pointer_tag());
3469  }
3470 
3471  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
3472  DCHECK_IMPLIES(element_size_log2 > 0, index().valid());
3473  DCHECK_IMPLIES(kind.maybe_unaligned,
3474  !SupportedOperations::IsUnalignedLoadSupported(stored_rep));
3475  DCHECK(LoadOp::OffsetIsValid(offset, kind.tagged_base));
3476  }
3477  static StoreOp& New(

3479  Kind kind, MemoryRepresentation stored_rep,

3486  maybe_indirect_pointer_tag);

3498 struct AllocateOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, AllocateOp> {

3566 struct JSStackCheckOp : OperationT<JSStackCheckOp> {
3567  enum class Kind : uint8_t { kFunctionEntry, kBuiltinEntry, kLoop };
3568  Kind kind;
3569 
3570  OpEffects Effects() const {
3571  switch (kind) {
3572  case Kind::kFunctionEntry:
3573  return OpEffects().CanCallAnything();
3574  case Kind::kBuiltinEntry:
3575  return OpEffects().CanCallAnything();
3576  case Kind::kLoop:
3577  // Loop body iteration stack checks can't write memory.
3578  // TODO(dmercadier): we could prevent this from allocating. In
3579  // particular, we'd need to:
3580  // - forbid GC interrupts from being processed in loop stack checks.
3581  // - make sure that the debugger always deopts the current function
3582  // when it triggers a loop interrupt.
3583  return OpEffects()
3584  .CanDependOnChecks()
3585  .CanDeopt()
3586  .CanReadHeapMemory()
3587  .CanAllocate();
3588  }
3589  }
3590 
3591  V<Context> native_context() const { return Base::input<Context>(0); }
3592  OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state() const {
3593  return input_count > 1 ? Base::input<FrameState>(1)
3594  : OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
3595  }
3596 
3597  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
3598 
3599  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
3600  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
3601  return {};
3602  }
3603 
3604  explicit JSStackCheckOp(V<Context> context, OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state,
3605  Kind kind)
3606  : Base(1 + frame_state.has_value()), kind(kind) {
3607  input(0) = context;
3608  if (frame_state.has_value()) {
3609  input(1) = frame_state.value();
3610  }
3611  }
3612 
3613  static JSStackCheckOp& New(Graph* graph, V<Context> context,
3614  OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state, Kind kind) {
3615  return Base::New(graph, 1 + frame_state.has_value(), context, frame_state,
3616  kind);
3617  }
3618 
3619  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
3620  DCHECK_EQ(kind == Kind::kBuiltinEntry, !frame_state().has_value());
3621  }
3622 
3623  template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
3624  V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
3625  return fn(mapper.Map(native_context()), mapper.Map(frame_state()), kind);
3626  }
3627 
3628  auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind}; }
3629 };

3734 struct FrameStateOp : OperationT<FrameStateOp> {
3735  bool inlined;
3736  const FrameStateData* data;
3737 
3738  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
3739  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
3740 
3741  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
3742  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
3743  return {};
3744  }
3745 
3746  V<FrameState> parent_frame_state() const {
3747  DCHECK(inlined);
3748  return input<FrameState>(0);
3749  }
3750  base::Vector<const OpIndex> state_values() const {
3751  base::Vector<const OpIndex> result = inputs();
3752  if (inlined) result += 1;
3753  return result;
3754  }
3755  uint16_t state_values_count() const {
3756  DCHECK_EQ(input_count - inlined, state_values().size());
3757  return input_count - inlined;
3758  }
3759  const OpIndex state_value(size_t idx) const { return state_values()[idx]; }
3760 
3761  RegisterRepresentation state_value_rep(size_t idx) const {
3762  return RegisterRepresentation::FromMachineRepresentation(
3763  data->machine_types[idx].representation());
3764  }
3765 
3766  FrameStateOp(base::Vector<const OpIndex> inputs, bool inlined,
3767  const FrameStateData* data)
3768  : Base(inputs), inlined(inlined), data(data) {}
3769 
3770  template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
3771  V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
3772  auto mapped_inputs = mapper.template Map<32>(inputs());
3773  return fn(base::VectorOf(mapped_inputs), inlined, data);
3774  }
3775 
3776  size_t hash_value(
3777  HashingStrategy strategy = HashingStrategy::kDefault) const {
3778  // Computing the full hash of {data} would be a bit slow, so we just use the
3779  // `bailout_id` and `inlined` (+ the inputs) to get a quick hash (and rely
3780  // on the == operator to properly check later if 2 FrameStateOp with the
3781  // same hash are really equal)
3782  return HashWithOptions(inlined, data->frame_state_info.bailout_id());
3783  }
3784 
3785  V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void Validate(const Graph& graph) const;
3786  V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
3787  auto options() const { return std::tuple{inlined, *data}; }
3788 };

3812 struct DeoptimizeIfOp : FixedArityOperationT<2, DeoptimizeIfOp> {
3813  bool negated;
3814  const DeoptimizeParameters* parameters;
3815 
3816  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanDeopt();
3817  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
3818 
3819  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
3820  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
3821  return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
3822  }
3823 
3824  V<Word32> condition() const { return input<Word32>(0); }
3825  V<FrameState> frame_state() const { return input<FrameState>(1); }
3826 
3827  DeoptimizeIfOp(V<Word32> condition, V<FrameState> frame_state, bool negated,
3828  const DeoptimizeParameters* parameters)
3829  : Base(condition, frame_state),
3830  negated(negated),
3831  parameters(parameters) {}
3832 
3833  bool EqualsForGVN(const DeoptimizeIfOp& other) const {
3834  // As far as GVN is concerned, the `frame_state` and `parameters` don't
3835  // matter: 2 DeoptimizeIf can be GVNed if they have the same `condition` and
3836  // same `negated`, regardless of their `frame_state` and `parameters`.
3837  return condition() == other.condition() && negated == other.negated;
3838  }
3839  size_t hash_value(
3840  HashingStrategy strategy = HashingStrategy::kDefault) const {
3841  // To enable GVNing as described above in `EqualsForGVN`, `hash_value` has
3842  // to ignore the `frame_state` and the `parameters`.
3843  return fast_hash_combine(Opcode::kDeoptimizeIf, condition(), negated);
3844  }
3845  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
3846  DCHECK(Get(graph, frame_state()).Is<FrameStateOp>());
3847  }
3848  auto options() const { return std::tuple{negated, parameters}; }
3849  void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
3850 };

3897 
3898  TrapIfOp(V<Word32> condition, OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state, bool negated,

3917  negated, trap_id);

3991 struct TSCallDescriptor : public NON_EXPORTED_BASE(ZoneObject) {
3992  const CallDescriptor* descriptor;
3993  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> in_reps;
3994  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> out_reps;
3995  CanThrow can_throw;
3996  LazyDeoptOnThrow lazy_deopt_on_throw;
3997  // TODO(dlehmann,353475584): Since the `JSWasmCallParameters` are specific to
3998  // one particular call site, this assumes that (only works correctly if)
3999  // `TSCallDescriptor`s are not shared across different calls (which they are
4000  // not at the moment).
4001  // For sharing call descriptors, the `JSWasmCallParameters` need to be moved
4002  // to the CallOp, which causes a lot of code churn (needs touching all
4003  // `REDUCE(Call)`).
4004  const JSWasmCallParameters* js_wasm_call_parameters;
4005 
4006  TSCallDescriptor(const CallDescriptor* descriptor,
4007  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> in_reps,
4008  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> out_reps,
4009  CanThrow can_throw, LazyDeoptOnThrow lazy_deopt_on_throw,
4010  const JSWasmCallParameters* js_wasm_call_parameters)
4011  : descriptor(descriptor),
4012  in_reps(in_reps),
4013  out_reps(out_reps),
4014  can_throw(can_throw),
4015  lazy_deopt_on_throw(lazy_deopt_on_throw),
4016  js_wasm_call_parameters(js_wasm_call_parameters) {}
4017 
4018  static const TSCallDescriptor* Create(
4019  const CallDescriptor* descriptor, CanThrow can_throw,
4020  LazyDeoptOnThrow lazy_deopt_on_throw, Zone* graph_zone,
4021  const JSWasmCallParameters* js_wasm_call_parameters = nullptr) {
4022  DCHECK_IMPLIES(can_throw == CanThrow::kNo,
4023  lazy_deopt_on_throw == LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo);
4024  base::Vector<RegisterRepresentation> in_reps =
4025  graph_zone->AllocateVector<RegisterRepresentation>(
4026  descriptor->ParameterCount());
4027  for (size_t i = 0; i < descriptor->ParameterCount(); ++i) {
4028  in_reps[i] = RegisterRepresentation::FromMachineRepresentation(
4029  descriptor->GetParameterType(i).representation());
4030  }
4031  base::Vector<RegisterRepresentation> out_reps =
4032  graph_zone->AllocateVector<RegisterRepresentation>(
4033  descriptor->ReturnCount());
4034  for (size_t i = 0; i < descriptor->ReturnCount(); ++i) {
4035  out_reps[i] = RegisterRepresentation::FromMachineRepresentation(
4036  descriptor->GetReturnType(i).representation());
4037  }
4038  return graph_zone->New<TSCallDescriptor>(descriptor, in_reps, out_reps,
4039  can_throw, lazy_deopt_on_throw,
4040  js_wasm_call_parameters);
4041  }
4042 };
4043 
4044 template <>
4045 struct fast_hash<TSCallDescriptor> {
4046  size_t operator()(const TSCallDescriptor& v) {
4047  const CallDescriptor& d = *v.descriptor;
4048  // This does not include all fields of the call descriptor, but it should be
4049  // sufficient to differentiate between different calls (and collisions are
4050  // not too critical).
4051  return fast_hash_combine(d.kind(), d.tag(), d.ReturnCount(),
4052  d.ParameterCount(), d.GPParameterCount(),
4053  d.FPParameterCount(), d.ParameterSlotCount(),
4054  d.ReturnSlotCount(), d.flags());
4055  }
4056 };

4059 std::optional<Builtin> TryGetBuiltinId(const ConstantOp* target,
4060  JSHeapBroker* broker);

4062 struct CallOp : OperationT<CallOp> {
4063  const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor;
4064  OpEffects callee_effects;
4065 
4066  OpEffects Effects() const { return callee_effects; }
4067 
4068  // The outputs are produced by the `DidntThrow` operation.
4069  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
4070  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> results_rep() const {
4071  return descriptor->out_reps;
4072  }
4073 
4074  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4075  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4076  storage.resize(input_count);
4077  size_t i = 0;
4078  if (descriptor->descriptor->IsCodeObjectCall() ||
4079  descriptor->descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall() ||
4080  descriptor->descriptor->IsBuiltinPointerCall()) {
4081  storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
4082 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4083  } else if (descriptor->descriptor->IsIndirectWasmFunctionCall()) {
4084  storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32();
4085 #endif
4086  } else {
4087  storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::WordPtr();
4088  }
4089  if (HasFrameState()) {
4090  storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::None();
4091  }
4092  for (auto rep : descriptor->in_reps) {
4093  // In JavaScript, parameters are optional.
4094  if (i >= input_count) break;
4095  storage[i++] = rep;
4096  }
4097  storage.resize(i);
4098  return base::VectorOf(storage);
4099  }
4100 
4101  bool HasFrameState() const {
4102  return descriptor->descriptor->NeedsFrameState();
4103  }
4104 
4105  V<CallTarget> callee() const { return input<CallTarget>(0); }
4106  OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state() const {
4107  return HasFrameState() ? input<FrameState>(1)
4108  : OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
4109  }
4110  base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments() const {
4111  return inputs().SubVector(1 + HasFrameState(), input_count);
4112  }
4113 
4114  CallOp(V<CallTarget> callee, OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state,
4115  base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
4116  const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor, OpEffects effects)
4117  : Base(1 + frame_state.valid() + arguments.size()),
4118  descriptor(descriptor),
4119  callee_effects(effects) {
4120  base::Vector<OpIndex> inputs = this->inputs();
4121  inputs[0] = callee;
4122  if (frame_state.valid()) {
4123  inputs[1] = frame_state.value();
4124  }
4125  inputs.SubVector(1 + frame_state.valid(), inputs.size())
4126  .OverwriteWith(arguments);
4127  }
4128 
4129  template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
4130  V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
4131  V<CallTarget> mapped_callee = mapper.Map(callee());
4132  OptionalV<FrameState> mapped_frame_state = mapper.Map(frame_state());
4133  auto mapped_arguments = mapper.template Map<16>(arguments());
4134  return fn(mapped_callee, mapped_frame_state,
4135  base::VectorOf(mapped_arguments), descriptor, Effects());
4136  }
4137 
4138  V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void Validate(const Graph& graph) const;
4139 
4140  static CallOp& New(Graph* graph, V<CallTarget> callee,
4141  OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state,
4142  base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
4143  const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor, OpEffects effects) {
4144  return Base::New(graph, 1 + frame_state.valid() + arguments.size(), callee,
4145  frame_state, arguments, descriptor, effects);
4146  }
4147  // TODO(mliedtke): Should the hash function be overwritten, so that calls (and
4148  // potentially tail calls) can participate in GVN? Right now this is prevented
4149  // by every call descriptor being a different pointer.
4150  auto options() const { return std::tuple{descriptor, callee_effects}; }
4151  size_t hash_value(HashingStrategy strategy = HashingStrategy::kDefault) const;
4152  void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
4153 };

4155 // Catch an exception from the first operation of the `successor` block and
4156 // continue execution in `catch_block` in this case.
4157 struct CheckExceptionOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, CheckExceptionOp> {
4158  Block* didnt_throw_block;

4167  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4168  return {};
4169  }

4172  Block* catch_block)
4173  : Base(throwing_operation),

4183 // This is a pseudo-operation that marks the beginning of a catch block. It
4184 // returns the caught exception.

4201 // Throwing operations always appear together with `DidntThrowOp`, which
4202 // produces the value in case that no exception was thrown. If the callsite is
4203 // non-catching, then `DidntThrowOp` follows right after the throwing operation:
4204 //
4205 // 100: Call(...)
4206 // 101: DidntThrow(100)
4207 // 102: Foo(101)
4208 //
4209 // If the callsite can catch, then the
4210 // pattern is as follows:
4211 //
4212 // 100: Call(...)
4213 // 101: CheckException(B10, B11)
4214 //
4215 // B10:
4216 // 102: DidntThrow(100)
4217 // 103: Foo(102)
4218 //
4219 // B11:
4220 // 200: CatchBlockBegin()
4221 // 201: ...
4222 //
4223 // This complexity is mostly hidden from graph creation, with
4224 // `DidntThrowOp` and `CheckExceptionOp` being inserted automatically.
4225 // The correct way to produce `CheckExceptionOp` is to create an
4226 // `Assembler::CatchScope`, which will cause all throwing operations
4227 // to add a `CheckExceptionOp` automatically while the scope is active.
4228 // Since `CopyingPhase` does this automatically, lowering throwing
4229 // operations into an arbitrary subgraph works automatically.
4230 struct DidntThrowOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, DidntThrowOp> {
4231  OpEffects throwing_op_effects;
4232 
4233  // If there is a `CheckException` operation with a catch block for
4234  // `throwing_operation`.
4235  bool has_catch_block;
4236  // This is a pointer to a vector instead of a vector to save a bit of memory,
4237  // using optimal 16 bytes instead of 24.
4238  const base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation>* results_rep;
4239 
4240  OpEffects Effects() const { return throwing_op_effects; }
4241 
4242  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
4243  return *results_rep;
4244  }
4245 
4246  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4247  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4248  return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::None()>();
4249  }
4250 
4251  OpIndex throwing_operation() const { return input(0); }
4252 
4253  explicit DidntThrowOp(
4254  OpIndex throwing_operation, bool has_catch_block,
4255  const base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation>* results_rep,
4256  OpEffects throwing_op_effects)
4257  : Base(throwing_operation),
4258  throwing_op_effects(throwing_op_effects),
4259  has_catch_block(has_catch_block),
4260  results_rep(results_rep) {}
4261  V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void Validate(const Graph& graph) const;
4262  auto options() const {
4263  return std::tuple{throwing_op_effects, has_catch_block};
4264  }
4265 };
4266 
4267 struct TailCallOp : OperationT<TailCallOp> {
4268  const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor;
4269 
4270  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
4271  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
4272  // While TailCalls do return some values, those values are returned to the
4273  // caller rather than to the current function (and a TailCallOp thus never
4274  // has any uses), so we set the outputs_rep to empty. If you need to know
4275  // what a TailCallOp returns, you can find out in `descriptor->outputs_rep`.
4276  return {};
4277  }
4278 
4279  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4280  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4281  storage.resize(input_count);
4282  size_t i = 0;
4283 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4284  if (descriptor->descriptor->IsIndirectWasmFunctionCall()) {
4285  storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32();
4286  } else if (descriptor->descriptor->IsDirectWasmFunctionCall() ||
4287  descriptor->descriptor->IsWasmImportWrapper() ||
4288  descriptor->descriptor->IsWasmCapiFunction()) {
4289  storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::WordPtr();
4290  } else {
4291  storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
4292  }
4293 #else
4294  storage[i++] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
4295 #endif
4296  for (auto rep : descriptor->in_reps) {
4297  storage[i++] = rep;
4298  }
4299  storage.resize(i);
4300  return base::VectorOf(storage);
4301  }
4302 
4303  OpIndex callee() const { return input(0); }
4304  base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments() const {
4305  return inputs().SubVector(1, input_count);
4306  }
4307 
4308  TailCallOp(OpIndex callee, base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
4309  const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor)
4310  : Base(1 + arguments.size()), descriptor(descriptor) {
4311  base::Vector<OpIndex> inputs = this->inputs();
4312  inputs[0] = callee;
4313  inputs.SubVector(1, inputs.size()).OverwriteWith(arguments);
4314  }
4315 
4316  template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
4317  V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
4318  OpIndex mapped_callee = mapper.Map(callee());
4319  auto mapped_arguments = mapper.template Map<16>(arguments());
4320  return fn(mapped_callee, base::VectorOf(mapped_arguments), descriptor);
4321  }
4322 
4323  static TailCallOp& New(Graph* graph, OpIndex callee,
4324  base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
4325  const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor) {
4326  return Base::New(graph, 1 + arguments.size(), callee, arguments,
4327  descriptor);
4328  }
4329  auto options() const { return std::tuple{descriptor}; }
4330  void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
4331 };

4340  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4341  return {};

4348 struct ReturnOp : OperationT<ReturnOp> {
4349  // spill_caller_frame_slots signals that all caller stack located return
4350  // values should be spilled before reaching the InstructionSelector.
4351  // The growable stacks implementation does extra work to spill these values
4352  // and it cannot be performed during InstructionSelector lowering efficiently.
4353  bool spill_caller_frame_slots;
4354  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
4355  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
4356 
4357  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4358  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4359  // TODO(mliedtke): Ideally, a return op would expect to get the correct
4360  // types for all its return values, not just the pop count.
4361  return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
4362  }
4363 
4364  // Number of additional stack slots to be removed.
4365  V<Word32> pop_count() const { return input<Word32>(0); }
4366 
4367  base::Vector<const OpIndex> return_values() const {
4368  return inputs().SubVector(1, input_count);
4369  }
4370 
4371  ReturnOp(V<Word32> pop_count, base::Vector<const OpIndex> return_values,
4372  bool spill_caller_frame_slots)
4373  : Base(1 + return_values.size()),
4374  spill_caller_frame_slots(spill_caller_frame_slots) {
4375  base::Vector<OpIndex> inputs = this->inputs();
4376  inputs[0] = pop_count;
4377  inputs.SubVector(1, inputs.size()).OverwriteWith(return_values);
4378  }
4379 
4380  template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
4381  V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
4382  OpIndex mapped_pop_count = mapper.Map(pop_count());
4383  auto mapped_return_values = mapper.template Map<4>(return_values());
4384  return fn(mapped_pop_count, base::VectorOf(mapped_return_values),
4385  spill_caller_frame_slots);
4386  }
4387 
4388  static ReturnOp& New(Graph* graph, V<Word32> pop_count,
4389  base::Vector<const OpIndex> return_values,
4390  bool spill_caller_frame_slots) {
4391  return Base::New(graph, 1 + return_values.size(), pop_count, return_values,
4392  spill_caller_frame_slots);
4393  }
4394  auto options() const { return std::tuple{spill_caller_frame_slots}; }
4395 };

4438 struct SwitchOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, SwitchOp> {
4439  struct Case {
4440  BranchHint hint;
4441  int32_t value;
4442  Block* destination;
4443 
4444  Case(int32_t value, Block* destination, BranchHint hint)
4445  : hint(hint), value(value), destination(destination) {}
4446 
4447  bool operator==(const Case& other) const {
4448  return value == other.value && destination == other.destination &&
4449  hint == other.hint;
4450  }
4451  };
4452  BranchHint default_hint;
4453  base::Vector<Case> cases;
4454  Block* default_case;
4455 
4456  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanChangeControlFlow();
4457  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
4458 
4459  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4460  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4461  return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
4462  }
4463 
4464  V<Word32> input() const { return Base::input<Word32>(0); }
4465 
4466  SwitchOp(V<Word32> input, base::Vector<Case> cases, Block* default_case,
4467  BranchHint default_hint)
4468  : Base(input),
4469  default_hint(default_hint),
4470  cases(cases),
4471  default_case(default_case) {}
4472 
4473  V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void Validate(const Graph& graph) const;
4474  void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
4475  size_t hash_value(HashingStrategy strategy = HashingStrategy::kDefault) const;
4476  auto options() const { return std::tuple{cases, default_case, default_hint}; }
4477 };

4479 template <>
4480 struct fast_hash<SwitchOp::Case> {
4481  size_t operator()(SwitchOp::Case v) {
4482  return fast_hash_combine(v.value, v.destination);
4483  }
4484 };
4485 
4486 inline base::SmallVector<Block*, 4> SuccessorBlocks(const Operation& op) {
4487  switch (op.opcode) {
4488  case Opcode::kCheckException: {
4489  auto& casted = op.Cast<CheckExceptionOp>();
4490  return {casted.didnt_throw_block, casted.catch_block};
4491  }
4492  case Opcode::kGoto: {
4493  auto& casted = op.Cast<GotoOp>();
4494  return {casted.destination};
4495  }
4496  case Opcode::kBranch: {
4497  auto& casted = op.Cast<BranchOp>();
4498  return {casted.if_true, casted.if_false};
4499  }
4500  case Opcode::kReturn:
4501  case Opcode::kTailCall:
4502  case Opcode::kDeoptimize:
4503  case Opcode::kUnreachable:
4504  return base::SmallVector<Block*, 4>{};
4505  case Opcode::kSwitch: {
4506  auto& casted = op.Cast<SwitchOp>();
4507  base::SmallVector<Block*, 4> result;
4508  for (const SwitchOp::Case& c : casted.cases) {
4509  result.push_back(c.destination);
4510  }
4511  result.push_back(casted.default_case);
4512  return result;
4513  }
4514 #define NON_TERMINATOR_CASE(op) case Opcode::k##op:
4515  TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST_NOT_BLOCK_TERMINATOR(NON_TERMINATOR_CASE)
4516  UNREACHABLE();
4517 #undef NON_TERMINATOR_CASE
4518  }
4519 }
4520 
4521 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE base::SmallVector<Block*, 4> SuccessorBlocks(
4522  const Block& block, const Graph& graph);

4769  enum class InputInterpretation : uint8_t {
4770  kSigned,
4771  kUnsigned,
4772  kDouble,
4773  kDoubleOrHole,
4774  kDoubleOrUndefined,
4775  kDoubleOrUndefinedOrHole,
4776  kCharCode,
4777  kCodePoint,
4778  };
4779  JSPrimitiveKind kind;
4780  RegisterRepresentation input_rep;
4781  InputInterpretation input_interpretation;
4782  CheckForMinusZeroMode minus_zero_mode;
4783 
4784  // The input is untagged and the results are identityless primitives.
4785  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanAllocateWithoutIdentity();
4786  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
4787  return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
4788  }
4789 
4790  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
4791  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
4792  return InputsRepFactory::SingleRep(input_rep);
4793  }
4794 
4795  V<Untagged> input() const { return Base::input<Untagged>(0); }
4796 
4797  ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp(V<Untagged> input, JSPrimitiveKind kind,
4798  RegisterRepresentation input_rep,
4799  InputInterpretation input_interpretation,
4800  CheckForMinusZeroMode minus_zero_mode)
4801  : Base(input),
4802  kind(kind),
4803  input_rep(input_rep),
4804  input_interpretation(input_interpretation),
4805  minus_zero_mode(minus_zero_mode) {
4806  DCHECK_EQ(input_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Float64(),
4807  (input_interpretation ==
4808  any_of(InputInterpretation::kDouble,
4809  InputInterpretation::kDoubleOrHole,
4810  InputInterpretation::kDoubleOrUndefined,
4811  InputInterpretation::kDoubleOrUndefinedOrHole)));
4812  }
4813 
4814  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
4815  switch (kind) {
4816  case JSPrimitiveKind::kBigInt:
4817  DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word64());
4818  DCHECK_EQ(minus_zero_mode,
4819  CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
4820  break;
4821  case JSPrimitiveKind::kBoolean:
4822  DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
4823  DCHECK_EQ(minus_zero_mode,
4824  CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
4825  break;
4826  case JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber:
4827  case JSPrimitiveKind::kHeapNumber:
4828  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
4829  minus_zero_mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero,
4830  input_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Float64());
4831  break;
4832  case JSPrimitiveKind::kHeapNumberOrUndefined:
4833  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
4834  minus_zero_mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero,
4835  input_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Float64());
4836  break;
4837  case JSPrimitiveKind::kSmi:
4838  DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, WordRepresentation::Word32());
4839  DCHECK_EQ(minus_zero_mode,
4840  CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
4841  break;
4842  case JSPrimitiveKind::kString:
4843  DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, WordRepresentation::Word32());
4844  DCHECK_EQ(input_interpretation,
4845  any_of(InputInterpretation::kCharCode,
4846  InputInterpretation::kCodePoint));
4847  break;
4848  }
4849  }
4850 
4851  auto options() const {
4852  return std::tuple{kind, input_rep, input_interpretation, minus_zero_mode};
4853  }
4854 };
4855 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::ostream& operator<<(
4856  std::ostream& os, ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind kind);

5277 // TODO(nicohartmann@): We should consider getting rid of the LoadFieldByIndex
5278 // operation.
5279 struct LoadFieldByIndexOp : FixedArityOperationT<2, LoadFieldByIndexOp> {
5280  static constexpr OpEffects effects =
5281  OpEffects()
5282  // Read the possibly mutable property.
5283  .CanReadHeapMemory()
5284  // We may allocate heap number for the result.
5285  .CanAllocateWithoutIdentity()
5286  // We assume the input is an object.
5287  .CanDependOnChecks();
5288  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
5289  return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
5290  }
5291 
5292  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
5293  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
5294  return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
5295  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
5296  }
5297 
5298  OpIndex object() const { return Base::input(0); }
5299  // Index encoding (see `src/objects/field-index-inl.h`):
5300  // For efficiency, the LoadByFieldIndex instruction takes an index that is
5301  // optimized for quick access. If the property is inline, the index is
5302  // positive. If it's out-of-line, the encoded index is -raw_index - 1 to
5303  // disambiguate the zero out-of-line index from the zero inobject case.
5304  // The index itself is shifted up by one bit, the lower-most bit
5305  // signifying if the field is a mutable double box (1) or not (0).
5306  OpIndex index() const { return Base::input(1); }
5307 
5308  LoadFieldByIndexOp(OpIndex object, OpIndex index) : Base(object, index) {}
5309 
5310  auto options() const { return std::tuple{}; }
5311 };

5328 struct DebugPrintOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, DebugPrintOp> {
5329  RegisterRepresentation rep;
5330 
5331  // We just need to ensure that the debug print stays in the same block and
5332  // observes the right memory state. It doesn't actually change control flow,
5333  // but pretending so ensures the we do not remove the debug print even though
5334  // it is unused. We assume that the debug print doesn't affect memory so that
5335  // the scheduling of loads is not affected.
5336  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects()
5337  .CanChangeControlFlow()
5338  .CanDependOnChecks()
5339  .CanReadMemory()
5340  .RequiredWhenUnused();
5341  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
5342 
5343  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
5344  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
5345  return InputsRepFactory::SingleRep(rep);
5346  }
5347 
5348  OpIndex input() const { return Base::input(0); }
5349 
5350  DebugPrintOp(OpIndex input, RegisterRepresentation rep)
5351  : Base(input), rep(rep) {}
5352 
5353  auto options() const { return std::tuple{rep}; }
5354 };

5366  kShiftLeft,
5367  kShiftRightArithmetic,
5368  };
5369  Kind kind;
5370 
5371  // These operations can deopt (abort), allocate and read immutable data.
5372  static constexpr OpEffects effects =
5373  OpEffects()
5374  // Allocate the resulting BigInt, which does not have identity.
5375  .CanAllocateWithoutIdentity()
5376  .CanDeopt();
5377  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
5378  return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
5379  }
5380 
5381  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
5382  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
5383  return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
5384  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
5385  }
5386 
5387  V<BigInt> left() const { return Base::input<BigInt>(0); }
5388  V<BigInt> right() const { return Base::input<BigInt>(1); }
5389  V<FrameState> frame_state() const { return Base::input<FrameState>(2); }
5390 
5391  BigIntBinopOp(V<BigInt> left, V<BigInt> right, V<FrameState> frame_state,
5392  Kind kind)
5393  : Base(left, right, frame_state), kind(kind) {}
5394  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
5395  DCHECK(Get(graph, frame_state()).Is<FrameStateOp>());
5396  }
5397 
5398  auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind}; }
5399 };
5400 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os,
5401  BigIntBinopOp::Kind kind);

5851 
5852 inline constexpr RegisterRepresentation RegisterRepresentationForArrayType(
5853  ExternalArrayType array_type) {
5854  switch (array_type) {
5855  case kExternalInt8Array:
5856  case kExternalUint8Array:
5857  case kExternalUint8ClampedArray:
5858  case kExternalInt16Array:
5859  case kExternalUint16Array:
5860  case kExternalInt32Array:
5861  case kExternalUint32Array:
5862  case kExternalFloat16Array:
5863  return RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
5864  case kExternalFloat32Array:
5865  return RegisterRepresentation::Float32();
5866  case kExternalFloat64Array:
5867  return RegisterRepresentation::Float64();
5868  case kExternalBigInt64Array:
5869  case kExternalBigUint64Array:
5870  return RegisterRepresentation::Word64();
5871  }
5872 }
5873 
5874 inline base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> VectorForRep(
5875  RegisterRepresentation rep) {
5876  static constexpr std::array<RegisterRepresentation, 6> table{
5877  RegisterRepresentation::Word32(), RegisterRepresentation::Word64(),
5878  RegisterRepresentation::Float32(), RegisterRepresentation::Float64(),
5879  RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), RegisterRepresentation::Compressed()};
5880  return base::VectorOf(&table[static_cast<size_t>(rep.value())], 1);
5881 }

5883 struct LoadTypedElementOp : FixedArityOperationT<4, LoadTypedElementOp> {
5884  ExternalArrayType array_type;
5885 
5886  static constexpr OpEffects effects =
5887  OpEffects()
5888  // We read mutable memory.
5889  .CanReadMemory()
5890  // We rely on the input type and a valid index.
5891  .CanDependOnChecks();

5893  return VectorForRep(RegisterRepresentationForArrayType(array_type));
5894  }

5897  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
5898  return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
5899  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
5900  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(),
5901  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::WordPtr()>();
5902  }
5903 
5904  OpIndex buffer() const { return Base::input(0); }
5905  OpIndex base() const { return Base::input(1); }
5906  OpIndex external() const { return Base::input(2); }
5907  OpIndex index() const { return Base::input(3); }

6006  ExternalArrayType array_type)
6007  : Base(buffer, base, external, index, value), array_type(array_type) {}

6052 struct TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp
6053  : FixedArityOperationT<3, TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp> {
6054  enum class Kind : uint8_t {
6055  kElement,
6056  kNumberElement,
6057  kOddballElement,
6058  kNonNumberElement,
6059  kSignedSmallElement,
6060  };
6061  Kind kind;
6062  MaybeIndirectHandle<Map> fast_map;
6063  MaybeIndirectHandle<Map> double_map;
6064 
6065  static constexpr OpEffects effects =
6066  OpEffects()
6067  // We are reading and writing mutable memory.
6068  .CanReadHeapMemory()
6069  .CanWriteHeapMemory()
6070  // We rely on the input type and a valid index.
6071  .CanDependOnChecks();
6072  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
6073 
6074  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
6075  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
6076  return InitVectorOf(
6077  storage, {RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
6078  RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(), value_representation()});
6079  }
6080 
6081  V<JSArray> array() const { return Base::input<JSArray>(0); }
6082  V<WordPtr> index() const { return Base::input<WordPtr>(1); }
6083  V<Any> value() const { return Base::input<Any>(2); }
6084 
6085  TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp(V<JSArray> array, V<WordPtr> index,
6086  V<Any> value, Kind kind,
6087  MaybeIndirectHandle<Map> fast_map,
6088  MaybeIndirectHandle<Map> double_map)
6089  : Base(array, index, value),
6090  kind(kind),
6091  fast_map(fast_map),
6092  double_map(double_map) {}
6093 
6094 
6095  RegisterRepresentation value_representation() const {
6096  switch (kind) {
6097  case Kind::kElement:
6098  case Kind::kNonNumberElement:
6099  case Kind::kOddballElement:
6100  return RegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
6101  case Kind::kNumberElement:
6102  return RegisterRepresentation::Float64();
6103  case Kind::kSignedSmallElement:
6104  return RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
6105  }
6106  }
6107 
6108  size_t hash_value(
6109  HashingStrategy strategy = HashingStrategy::kDefault) const {
6110  DCHECK_EQ(strategy, HashingStrategy::kDefault);
6111  return HashWithOptions(fast_map.address(), double_map.address());
6112  }
6113 
6114  bool operator==(const TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp& other) const {
6115  return kind == other.kind && fast_map.equals(other.fast_map) &&
6116  double_map.equals(other.double_map);
6117  }
6118 
6119  auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind, fast_map, double_map}; }
6120 };

6123  std::ostream& os, TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind kind);

6216  mapper.Map(map()), maps, flags, feedback);
6217  }

6224  maps, flags, feedback);

6228 // AssumeMaps are inserted after CheckMaps have been lowered, in order to keep
6229 // map information around and easily accessible for subsequent optimization
6230 // passes (Load Elimination for instance can then use those AssumeMap to
6231 // determine that some objects don't alias because they have different maps).
6232 struct AssumeMapOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, AssumeMapOp> {
6233  ZoneRefSet<Map> maps;
6234  // AssumeMap should not be scheduled before the preceding CheckMaps
6235  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects()
6236  .CanDependOnChecks()
6237  .CanReadHeapMemory()
6238  .CanChangeControlFlow();
6239  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
6240 
6241  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
6242  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
6243  return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
6244  }
6245 
6246  V<HeapObject> heap_object() const { return Base::input<HeapObject>(0); }
6247 
6248  AssumeMapOp(V<HeapObject> heap_object, ZoneRefSet<Map> maps)
6249  : Base(heap_object), maps(std::move(maps)) {}
6250 
6251 
6252  auto options() const { return std::tuple{maps}; }
6253  void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
6254 };

6418 struct FastApiCallParameters : public NON_EXPORTED_BASE(ZoneObject) {

6424  : c_function(c_function) {}

6431 
6432 struct FastApiCallOp : OperationT<FastApiCallOp> {
6433  static constexpr uint32_t kSuccessValue = 1;
6434  static constexpr uint32_t kFailureValue = 0;
6435 
6436  const FastApiCallParameters* parameters;
6437  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> out_reps;
6438  LazyDeoptOnThrow lazy_deopt_on_throw;
6439 
6440  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanCallAnything();
6441 
6442  // There are three inputs that are not parameters, the frame state, the data
6443  // argument, and the context.
6444  static constexpr int kNumNonParamInputs = 3;
6445 
6446  // The outputs are produced by the `DidntThrow` operation.
6447  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const { return {}; }
6448 
6449  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
6450  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
6451  DCHECK_EQ(inputs().size(),
6452  kNumNonParamInputs + parameters->c_signature()->ArgumentCount());
6453  storage.resize(inputs().size());
6454  storage[0] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::None();
6455  storage[1] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
6456  storage[2] = MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
6457  for (unsigned i = 0; i < parameters->c_signature()->ArgumentCount(); ++i) {
6458  storage[i + kNumNonParamInputs] = argument_representation(i);
6459  }
6460  return base::VectorOf(storage);
6461  }
6462 
6463  MaybeRegisterRepresentation argument_representation(
6464  unsigned argument_index) const {
6465  const CTypeInfo& arg_type =
6466  parameters->c_signature()->ArgumentInfo(argument_index);
6467  uint8_t flags = static_cast<uint8_t>(arg_type.GetFlags());
6468  START_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
6469  switch (arg_type.GetSequenceType()) {
6470  case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kScalar:
6471  if (flags & (static_cast<uint8_t>(CTypeInfo::Flags::kEnforceRangeBit) |
6472  static_cast<uint8_t>(CTypeInfo::Flags::kClampBit))) {
6473  return MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Float64();
6474  }
6475  switch (arg_type.GetType()) {
6476  case CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid:
6477  UNREACHABLE();
6478  case CTypeInfo::Type::kBool:
6479  case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint8:
6480  case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt32:
6481  case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint32:
6482  return MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word32();
6483  case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt64:
6484  case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint64:
6485  return MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Word64();
6486  case CTypeInfo::Type::kV8Value:
6487  case CTypeInfo::Type::kApiObject:
6488  case CTypeInfo::Type::kPointer:
6489  case CTypeInfo::Type::kSeqOneByteString:
6490  return MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
6491  case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat32:
6492  case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat64:
6493  return MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Float64();
6494  case CTypeInfo::Type::kAny:
6495  // As the register representation is unknown, just treat it as None
6496  // to prevent any validation.
6497  return MaybeRegisterRepresentation::None();
6498  }
6499  case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kIsSequence:
6500  return MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
6501  case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kIsArrayBuffer:
6502  UNREACHABLE();
6503  }
6504  END_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
6505  }
6506 
6507  V<FrameState> frame_state() const { return input<FrameState>(0); }
6508 
6509  V<Object> data_argument() const { return input<Object>(1); }
6510 
6511  V<Context> context() const { return input<Context>(2); }
6512 
6513  base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments() const {
6514  return inputs().SubVector(kNumNonParamInputs, inputs().size());
6515  }
6516 
6517  FastApiCallOp(V<FrameState> frame_state, V<Object> data_argument,
6518  V<Context> context, base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
6519  const FastApiCallParameters* parameters,
6520  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> out_reps)
6521  : Base(kNumNonParamInputs + arguments.size()),
6522  parameters(parameters),
6523  out_reps(out_reps),
6524  lazy_deopt_on_throw(LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo) {
6525  base::Vector<OpIndex> inputs = this->inputs();
6526  inputs[0] = frame_state;
6527  inputs[1] = data_argument;
6528  inputs[2] = context;
6529  inputs.SubVector(kNumNonParamInputs, kNumNonParamInputs + arguments.size())
6530  .OverwriteWith(arguments);
6531  }
6532 
6533  template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
6534  V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
6535  V<FrameState> mapped_frame_state = mapper.Map(frame_state());
6536  OpIndex mapped_data_argument = mapper.Map(data_argument());
6537  V<Context> mapped_context = mapper.Map(context());
6538  auto mapped_arguments = mapper.template Map<8>(arguments());
6539  return fn(mapped_frame_state, mapped_data_argument, mapped_context,
6540  base::VectorOf(mapped_arguments), parameters, out_reps);
6541  }
6542 
6543 
6544  static FastApiCallOp& New(
6545  Graph* graph, V<FrameState> frame_state, V<Object> data_argument,
6546  V<Context> context, base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
6547  const FastApiCallParameters* parameters,
6548  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> out_reps) {
6549  return Base::New(graph, kNumNonParamInputs + arguments.size(), frame_state,
6550  data_argument, context, arguments, parameters, out_reps);
6551  }
6552 
6553  // out_reps[0] is always word32.
6554  auto options() const {
6555  DCHECK_EQ(out_reps[0], RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
6556  return std::tuple{parameters, out_reps[1], lazy_deopt_on_throw};
6557  }
6558 };

6712  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();

6944 struct WasmTypeCheckOp : OperationT<WasmTypeCheckOp> {
6945  WasmTypeCheckConfig config;
6946 
6947  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects().AssumesConsistentHeap();
6948 
6949  WasmTypeCheckOp(V<Object> object, OptionalV<Map> rtt,
6950  WasmTypeCheckConfig config)
6951  : Base(1 + rtt.valid()), config(config) {
6952  input(0) = object;
6953  if (rtt.valid()) {
6954  input(1) = rtt.value();
6955  }
6956  }
6957 
6958  template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
6959  V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
6960  return fn(mapper.Map(object()), mapper.Map(rtt()), config);
6961  }
6962 
6963  V<Object> object() const { return Base::input<Object>(0); }
6964  OptionalV<Map> rtt() const {
6965  return input_count > 1 ? input<Map>(1) : OptionalV<Map>::Nullopt();
6966  }
6967 
6968  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
6969  return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Word32()>();
6970  }
6971 
6972  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
6973  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
6974  return input_count > 1
6975  ? MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
6976  MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>()
6977  : MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
6978  }
6979 
6980 
6981  auto options() const { return std::tuple{config}; }
6982 
6983  static WasmTypeCheckOp& New(Graph* graph, V<Object> object,
6984  OptionalV<Map> rtt, WasmTypeCheckConfig config) {
6985  return Base::New(graph, 1 + rtt.valid(), object, rtt, config);
6986  }

7109 struct StructGetOp : FixedArityOperationT<1, StructGetOp> {
7110  bool is_signed; // `false` only for unsigned packed type accesses.
7111  CheckForNull null_check;
7112  const wasm::StructType* type;
7113  wasm::ModuleTypeIndex type_index;
7114  int field_index;
7115  std::optional<AtomicMemoryOrder> memory_order;
7116 
7117  OpEffects Effects() const {
7118  OpEffects result =
7119  OpEffects()
7120  // This should not float above a protective null check.
7121  .CanDependOnChecks()
7122  .CanReadMemory();
7123  if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
7124  // This may trap.
7125  result = result.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
7126  }
7127  if (memory_order.has_value()) {
7128  // Pretending that the op can write prevents reordering.
7129  result = result.CanWriteMemory();
7130  }
7131  return result;
7132  }
7133 
7134  StructGetOp(V<WasmStructNullable> object, const wasm::StructType* type,
7135  wasm::ModuleTypeIndex type_index, int field_index, bool is_signed,
7136  CheckForNull null_check,
7137  std::optional<AtomicMemoryOrder> memory_order)
7138  : Base(object),
7139  is_signed(is_signed),
7140  null_check(null_check),
7141  type(type),
7142  type_index(type_index),
7143  field_index(field_index),
7144  memory_order(memory_order) {}
7145 
7146  V<WasmStructNullable> object() const { return input<WasmStructNullable>(0); }
7147 
7148  bool is_atomic() const { return memory_order.has_value(); }
7149 
7150  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
7151  return base::VectorOf(&RepresentationFor(type->field(field_index)), 1);
7152  }
7153 
7154  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
7155  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
7156  return MaybeRepVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation::Tagged()>();
7157  }
7158 
7159  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
7160  DCHECK_LT(field_index, type->field_count());
7161  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!is_signed, type->field(field_index).is_packed());
7162  }
7163 
7164  auto options() const {
7165  return std::tuple{type, type_index, field_index,
7166  is_signed, null_check, memory_order};
7167  }
7168 
7169  void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
7170 };
7171 
7172 struct StructSetOp : FixedArityOperationT<2, StructSetOp> {
7173  CheckForNull null_check;
7174  const wasm::StructType* type;
7175  // TODO(jkummerow): If we stored the ValueType here, that would save a few
7176  // lookups later.
7177  wasm::ModuleTypeIndex type_index;
7178  int field_index;
7179  std::optional<AtomicMemoryOrder> memory_order;
7180 
7181  OpEffects Effects() const {
7182  OpEffects result =
7183  OpEffects()
7184  // This should not float above a protective null check.
7185  .CanDependOnChecks()
7186  .CanWriteMemory();
7187  if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
7188  // This may trap.
7189  result = result.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
7190  }
7191  return result;
7192  }
7193 
7194  StructSetOp(V<WasmStructNullable> object, V<Any> value,
7195  const wasm::StructType* type, wasm::ModuleTypeIndex type_index,
7196  int field_index, CheckForNull null_check,
7197  std::optional<AtomicMemoryOrder> memory_order)

7203  memory_order(memory_order) {}
7204 
7205  V<WasmStructNullable> object() const { return input<WasmStructNullable>(0); }
7206  V<Any> value() const { return input(1); }
7207

7209

7211  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {

7214  storage[1] = RepresentationFor(type->field(field_index));

7218  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
7219  DCHECK_LT(field_index, type->field_count());

7221 
7222  auto options() const {
7223  return std::tuple{type, type_index, field_index, null_check, memory_order};
7224  }
7225 
7226  void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
7227 };
7228 
7229 struct StructAtomicRMWOp : OperationT<StructAtomicRMWOp> {
7230  using BinOp = AtomicRMWOp::BinOp;
7231  BinOp bin_op;
7232  CheckForNull null_check;
7233  const wasm::StructType* type;
7234  wasm::ModuleTypeIndex type_index;
7235  int field_index;
7236  AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order;
7237 
7238  OpEffects Effects() const {
7239  OpEffects result =
7240  OpEffects()
7241  // This should not float above a protective null check.
7242  .CanDependOnChecks()
7243  .CanReadMemory()
7244  .CanWriteMemory();
7245  if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
7246  // This may trap.
7247  result = result.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
7248  }
7249  return result;
7250  }
7251 
7252  StructAtomicRMWOp(V<WasmStructNullable> object, OpIndex value,
7253  OptionalOpIndex expected, BinOp bin_op,
7254  const wasm::StructType* type,
7255  wasm::ModuleTypeIndex type_index, int field_index,
7256  CheckForNull null_check, AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order)
7257  : Base(2 + expected.valid()),
7258  bin_op(bin_op),
7259  null_check(null_check),
7260  type(type),
7261  type_index(type_index),
7262  field_index(field_index),
7263  memory_order(memory_order) {
7264  input(0) = object;
7265  input(1) = value;
7266  if (expected.valid()) {
7267  input(2) = expected.value();
7268  }
7269  }
7270 
7271  template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
7272  V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
7273  return fn(mapper.Map(object()), mapper.Map(value()), mapper.Map(expected()),
7274  bin_op, type, type_index, field_index, null_check, memory_order);
7275  }
7276 
7277  static StructAtomicRMWOp& New(Graph* graph, V<WasmStructNullable> object,
7278  V<Any> value, OptionalOpIndex expected,
7279  BinOp bin_op, const wasm::StructType* type,
7280  wasm::ModuleTypeIndex type_index,
7281  int field_index, CheckForNull null_check,
7282  AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order) {
7283  return Base::New(graph, 2 + expected.valid(), object, value, expected,
7284  bin_op, type, type_index, field_index, null_check,
7285  memory_order);
7286  }
7287 
7288  V<WasmStructNullable> object() const { return input<WasmStructNullable>(0); }
7289  V<Any> value() const { return input(1); }
7290  OptionalOpIndex expected() const {
7291  return input_count == 3 ? input(2) : OpIndex::Invalid();
7292  }
7293 
7294  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
7295  return base::VectorOf(&RepresentationFor(type->field(field_index)), 1);
7296  }
7297 
7298  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
7299  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
7300  if (bin_op == BinOp::kCompareExchange) {
7301  return InitVectorOf(storage,
7302  {RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
7303  RepresentationFor(type->field(field_index)),
7304  RepresentationFor(type->field(field_index))});
7305  }
7306  return InitVectorOf(storage, {RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
7307  RepresentationFor(type->field(field_index))});
7308  }
7309 
7310  void Validate(const Graph& graph) const {
7311  DCHECK_LT(field_index, type->field_count());
7312  DCHECK(type->field(field_index) == wasm::kWasmI32 ||
7313  type->field(field_index) == wasm::kWasmI64 ||
7314  (type->field(field_index).is_reference() &&
7315  bin_op == BinOp::kExchange));
7316  DCHECK_EQ(bin_op == BinOp::kCompareExchange, expected().valid());
7317  }
7318 
7319  auto options() const {
7320  return std::tuple{bin_op, type, type_index,
7321  field_index, null_check, memory_order};
7322  }
7323 };

7399 struct ArrayAtomicRMWOp : OperationT<ArrayAtomicRMWOp> {

7403  AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order;
7404

7406  return OpEffects()
7407  // This should not float above a protective null check.
7408  .CanDependOnChecks()
7409  .CanReadMemory()
7410  .CanWriteMemory();
7411  }
7412 
7413  ArrayAtomicRMWOp(V<WasmArrayNullable> array, V<Word32> index, OpIndex value,
7414  OptionalV<Any> expected, BinOp bin_op,
7415  wasm::ValueType element_type, AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order)

7417  bin_op(bin_op),
7418  element_type(element_type),
7419  memory_order(memory_order) {
7420  input(0) = array;
7421  input(1) = index;
7422  input(2) = value;
7423  if (expected.valid()) {
7424  input(3) = expected.value();
7425  }
7426  }

7428  template <typename Fn, typename Mapper>
7429  V8_INLINE auto Explode(Fn fn, Mapper& mapper) const {
7430  return fn(mapper.Map(array()), mapper.Map(index()), mapper.Map(value()),
7431  mapper.Map(expected()), bin_op, element_type, memory_order);
7432  }
7433 
7434  static ArrayAtomicRMWOp& New(Graph* graph, V<WasmArrayNullable> array,
7435  V<Word32> index, OpIndex value,
7436  OptionalV<Any> expected, BinOp bin_op,
7437  wasm::ValueType element_type,
7438  AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order) {
7439  return Base::New(graph, 3 + expected.valid(), array, index, value, expected,
7440  bin_op, element_type, memory_order);

7445  V<Any> value() const { return input<Any>(2); }

7447  return input_count == 4 ? input(3) : OpIndex::Invalid();
7448  }

7451  return base::VectorOf(&RepresentationFor(element_type), 1);
7452  }
7453

7455  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
7456  if (bin_op == BinOp::kCompareExchange) {
7457  return InitVectorOf(
7458  storage,
7459  {RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), RegisterRepresentation::Word32(),
7460  RepresentationFor(element_type), RepresentationFor(element_type)});
7461  }
7462  return InitVectorOf(storage, {RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
7463  RegisterRepresentation::Word32(),
7464  RepresentationFor(element_type)});
7465  }
7466

7468  DCHECK(element_type == wasm::kWasmI32 || element_type == wasm::kWasmI64 ||

7470  DCHECK_EQ(bin_op == BinOp::kCompareExchange, expected().valid());
7471  }

7474  return std::tuple{bin_op, element_type, memory_order};
7475  }

7811 struct Simd128BinopOp : FixedArityOperationT<2, Simd128BinopOp> {
7812  // clang-format off
7813  enum class Kind : uint8_t {
7814 #define DEFINE_KIND(kind) k##kind,
7815  FOREACH_SIMD_128_BINARY_OPCODE(DEFINE_KIND)
7816  kFirstSignExtensionOp = kI16x8ExtMulLowI8x16S,
7817  kLastSignExtensionOp = kI64x2ExtMulHighI32x4U,
7818 #undef DEFINE_KIND
7819  };
7820  // clang-format on
7821 
7822  Kind kind;
7823 
7824  static bool IsCommutative(Kind kind) {
7825  switch (kind) {
7826  // TODO(14108): Explicitly list all commutative SIMD operations.
7827  case Kind::kI64x2Add:
7828  case Kind::kI32x4Add:
7829  case Kind::kI16x8Add:
7830  case Kind::kI8x16Add:
7831  case Kind::kF64x2Add:
7832  case Kind::kF32x4Add:
7833 
7834  case Kind::kI64x2Mul:
7835  case Kind::kI32x4Mul:
7836  case Kind::kI16x8Mul:
7837  case Kind::kF64x2Mul:
7838  case Kind::kF32x4Mul:
7839 
7840  case Kind::kS128Xor:
7841  return true;
7842  default:
7843  return false;
7844  }
7845  }
7846 
7847  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
7848

7850  return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Simd128()>();

7856  RegisterRepresentation::Simd128()>();
7857  }

8382  case Kind::kI8x16:
8383  case Kind::kI16x8:
8384  case Kind::kI32x4:
8385  return RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
8386  case Kind::kI64x2:
8387  return RegisterRepresentation::Word64();
8388  case Kind::kF16x8:
8389  case Kind::kF32x4:
8390  return RegisterRepresentation::Float32();
8391  case Kind::kF64x2:
8392  return RegisterRepresentation::Float64();
8393  }
8394  }
8395 };
8396 
8397 // If `mode` is `kLoad`, load a value from `base() + index() + offset`, whose
8398 // size is determinded by `lane_kind`, and return the Simd128 `value()` with
8399 // the lane specified by `lane_kind` and `lane` replaced with the loaded value.
8400 // If `mode` is `kStore`, extract the lane specified by `lane` with size
8401 // `lane_kind` from `value()`, and store it to `base() + index() + offset`.
8402 struct Simd128LaneMemoryOp : FixedArityOperationT<3, Simd128LaneMemoryOp> {
8403  enum class Mode : bool { kLoad, kStore };
8404  using Kind = LoadOp::Kind;
8405  // The values encode the element_size_log2.
8406  enum class LaneKind : uint8_t { k8 = 0, k16 = 1, k32 = 2, k64 = 3 };
8407 
8408  Mode mode;
8409  Kind kind;
8410  LaneKind lane_kind;
8411  uint8_t lane;
8412  int offset;
8413 
8414  OpEffects Effects() const {
8415  OpEffects effects = mode == Mode::kLoad ? OpEffects().CanReadMemory()
8416  : OpEffects().CanWriteMemory();
8417  effects = effects.CanDependOnChecks();
8418  if (kind.with_trap_handler) effects = effects.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
8419  return effects;
8420  }
8421 
8422  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
8423  return mode == Mode::kLoad ? RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Simd128()>()
8424  : RepVector<>();
8425  }
8426 
8427  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
8428  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
8429  return MaybeRepVector<RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(),
8430  RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(),
8431  RegisterRepresentation::Simd128()>();
8432  }
8433 
8434  Simd128LaneMemoryOp(OpIndex base, OpIndex index, OpIndex value, Mode mode,
8435  Kind kind, LaneKind lane_kind, uint8_t lane, int offset)
8436  : Base(base, index, value),
8437  mode(mode),
8438  kind(kind),
8439  lane_kind(lane_kind),
8440  lane(lane),
8441  offset(offset) {}
8442 
8443  OpIndex base() const { return input(0); }
8444  OpIndex index() const { return input(1); }
8445  OpIndex value() const { return input(2); }
8446  uint8_t lane_size() const { return 1 << static_cast<uint8_t>(lane_kind); }
8447 
8448  void Validate(const Graph& graph) {
8449  DCHECK(!kind.tagged_base);
8450 #if DEBUG
8451  uint8_t lane_count;
8452  switch (lane_kind) {
8453  case LaneKind::k8:
8454  lane_count = 16;
8455  break;
8456  case LaneKind::k16:
8457  lane_count = 8;
8458  break;
8459  case LaneKind::k32:
8460  lane_count = 4;
8461  break;
8462  case LaneKind::k64:
8463  lane_count = 2;
8464  break;
8465  }
8466  DCHECK_LT(lane, lane_count);
8467 #endif
8468  }
8469 
8470  auto options() const {
8471  return std::tuple{mode, kind, lane_kind, lane, offset};
8472  }
8473  void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
8474 };

8476 #define FOREACH_SIMD_128_LOAD_TRANSFORM_OPCODE(V) \
8477  V(8x8S) \
8478  V(8x8U) \
8479  V(16x4S) \
8480  V(16x4U) \
8481  V(32x2S) \
8482  V(32x2U) \
8483  V(8Splat) \
8484  V(16Splat) \
8485  V(32Splat) \
8486  V(64Splat) \
8487  V(32Zero) \
8488  V(64Zero)
8489 
8490 // Load a value from `base() + index() + offset`, whose size is determinded by
8491 // `transform_kind`, and generate a Simd128 value as follows:
8492 // - From 8x8S to 32x2U (extend kinds), the loaded value has size 8. It is
8493 // interpreted as a vector of values according to the size of the kind, which
8494 // populate the even lanes of the generated value. The odd lanes are zero- or
8495 // sign-extended according to the kind.
8496 // - For splat kinds, the loaded value's size is determined by the kind, all
8497 // lanes of the generated value are populated with the loaded value.
8498 // - For "zero" kinds, the loaded value's size is determined by the kind, and
8499 // the generated value zero-extends the loaded value.
8500 struct Simd128LoadTransformOp
8501  : FixedArityOperationT<2, Simd128LoadTransformOp> {
8502  using LoadKind = LoadOp::Kind;
8503  enum class TransformKind : uint8_t {
8504 #define DEFINE_KIND(kind) k##kind,
8505  FOREACH_SIMD_128_LOAD_TRANSFORM_OPCODE(DEFINE_KIND)
8506 #undef DEFINE_KIND
8507  };
8508 
8509  LoadKind load_kind;
8510  TransformKind transform_kind;
8511  int offset;
8512 
8513  OpEffects Effects() const {
8514  OpEffects effects = OpEffects().CanReadMemory().CanDependOnChecks();
8515  if (load_kind.with_trap_handler) {
8516  effects = effects.CanLeaveCurrentFunction();
8517  }
8518  return effects;
8519  }
8520 
8521  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
8522  return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Simd128()>();
8523  }
8524 
8525  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
8526  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
8527  return MaybeRepVector<RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr(),
8528  RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr()>();
8529  }
8530 
8531  Simd128LoadTransformOp(V<WordPtr> base, V<WordPtr> index, LoadKind load_kind,
8532  TransformKind transform_kind, int offset)
8533  : Base(base, index),
8534  load_kind(load_kind),
8535  transform_kind(transform_kind),
8536  offset(offset) {}
8537 
8538  V<WordPtr> base() const { return input<WordPtr>(0); }
8539  V<WordPtr> index() const { return input<WordPtr>(1); }
8540 
8541  void Validate(const Graph& graph) { DCHECK(!load_kind.tagged_base); }
8542 
8543  auto options() const { return std::tuple{load_kind, transform_kind, offset}; }
8544  void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
8545 };
8546 
8547 // Takes two Simd128 inputs and generates a Simd128 value. The 8-bit lanes of
8548 // both inputs are numbered 0-31, and each output 8-bit lane is selected from
8549 // among the input lanes according to `shuffle`.
8550 struct Simd128ShuffleOp : FixedArityOperationT<2, Simd128ShuffleOp> {
8551  enum class Kind : uint8_t {
8552  kI8x2,
8553  kI8x4,
8554  kI8x8,
8555  kI8x16,
8556  };
8557 
8558  uint8_t shuffle[kSimd128Size] = {0};
8559  const Kind kind;
8560 
8561  static constexpr OpEffects effects = OpEffects();
8562 
8563  base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation> outputs_rep() const {
8564  return RepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Simd128()>();
8565  }
8566 
8567  base::Vector<const MaybeRegisterRepresentation> inputs_rep(
8568  ZoneVector<MaybeRegisterRepresentation>& storage) const {
8569  return MaybeRepVector<RegisterRepresentation::Simd128(),
8570  RegisterRepresentation::Simd128()>();
8571  }
8572 
8573  Simd128ShuffleOp(V<Simd128> left, V<Simd128> right, Kind kind,
8574  const uint8_t incoming_shuffle[kSimd128Size])
8575  : Base(left, right), kind(kind) {
8576  uint8_t count = 0;
8577  switch (kind) {
8578  default:
8579  UNREACHABLE();
8580  case Kind::kI8x2:
8581  count = 2;
8582  break;
8583  case Kind::kI8x4:
8584  count = 4;
8585  break;
8586  case Kind::kI8x8:
8587  count = 8;
8588  break;
8589  case Kind::kI8x16:
8590  count = 16;
8591  break;
8592  }
8593  std::copy_n(incoming_shuffle, count, shuffle);
8594  }
8595 
8596  V<Simd128> left() const { return input<Simd128>(0); }
8597  V<Simd128> right() const { return input<Simd128>(1); }
8598 
8599  void Validate(const Graph& graph) {
8600 #if DEBUG
8601  constexpr uint8_t kNumberOfLanesForShuffle = 32;
8602  for (uint8_t index : shuffle) {
8603  DCHECK_LT(index, kNumberOfLanesForShuffle);
8604  }
8605 #endif
8606  }
8607 
8608  auto options() const { return std::tuple{kind, shuffle}; }
8609  void PrintOptions(std::ostream& os) const;
8610 };

9342 #define OPERATION_EFFECTS_CASE(Name) Name##Op::EffectsIfStatic(),
9343 static constexpr std::optional<OpEffects>
9344  kOperationEffectsTable[kNumberOfOpcodes] = {
9345  TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST(OPERATION_EFFECTS_CASE)};
9346 #undef OPERATION_EFFECTS_CASE

9348 template <class Op>

9352 struct opcode_to_operation_map {};

9354 #define OPERATION_OPCODE_MAP_CASE(Name) \
9355  template <> \
9356  struct opcode_to_operation_map<Opcode::k##Name> { \
9357  using Op = Name##Op; \
9358  };
9359 TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST(OPERATION_OPCODE_MAP_CASE)

9362 template <class Op, class = void>
9363 struct static_operation_input_count : std::integral_constant<uint32_t, 0> {};
9364 template <class Op>
9365 struct static_operation_input_count<Op, std::void_t<decltype(Op::inputs)>>
9366  : std::integral_constant<uint32_t, sizeof(Op::inputs) / sizeof(OpIndex)> {};
9367 constexpr size_t kOperationSizeTable[kNumberOfOpcodes] = {
9368 #define OPERATION_SIZE(Name) sizeof(Name##Op),
9369  TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST(OPERATION_SIZE)
9370 #undef OPERATION_SIZE
9371 };
9372 constexpr size_t kOperationSizeDividedBySizeofOpIndexTable[kNumberOfOpcodes] = {
9373 #define OPERATION_SIZE(Name) (sizeof(Name##Op) / sizeof(OpIndex)),
9374  TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST(OPERATION_SIZE)
9375 #undef OPERATION_SIZE
9376 };

9378 inline base::Vector<const OpIndex> Operation::inputs() const {
9379  // This is actually undefined behavior, since we use the `this` pointer to
9380  // access an adjacent object.
9381  const OpIndex* ptr = reinterpret_cast<const OpIndex*>(
9382  reinterpret_cast<const char*>(this) +
9383  kOperationSizeTable[OpcodeIndex(opcode)]);
9384  return {ptr, input_count};
9385 }
9386 
9387 inline OpEffects Operation::Effects() const {
9388  if (auto prop = kOperationEffectsTable[OpcodeIndex(opcode)]) {
9389  return *prop;
9390  }
9391  switch (opcode) {
9392  case Opcode::kLoad:
9393  return Cast<LoadOp>().Effects();
9394  case Opcode::kStore:
9395  return Cast<StoreOp>().Effects();
9396  case Opcode::kCall:
9397  return Cast<CallOp>().Effects();
9398  case Opcode::kDidntThrow:
9399  return Cast<DidntThrowOp>().Effects();
9400  case Opcode::kTaggedBitcast:
9401  return Cast<TaggedBitcastOp>().Effects();
9402  case Opcode::kAtomicRMW:
9403  return Cast<AtomicRMWOp>().Effects();
9404  case Opcode::kAtomicWord32Pair:
9405  return Cast<AtomicWord32PairOp>().Effects();
9406  case Opcode::kJSStackCheck:
9407  return Cast<JSStackCheckOp>().Effects();
9408 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
9409  case Opcode::kWasmStackCheck:
9410  return Cast<WasmStackCheckOp>().Effects();
9411  case Opcode::kStructGet:
9412  return Cast<StructGetOp>().Effects();
9413  case Opcode::kStructSet:
9414  return Cast<StructSetOp>().Effects();
9415  case Opcode::kStructAtomicRMW:
9416  return Cast<StructAtomicRMWOp>().Effects();
9417  case Opcode::kArrayAtomicRMW:
9418  return Cast<ArrayAtomicRMWOp>().Effects();
9419  case Opcode::kArrayLength:
9420  return Cast<ArrayLengthOp>().Effects();
9421  case Opcode::kSimd128LaneMemory:
9422  return Cast<Simd128LaneMemoryOp>().Effects();
9423  case Opcode::kSimd128LoadTransform:
9424  return Cast<Simd128LoadTransformOp>().Effects();
9425 #if V8_ENABLE_WASM_DEINTERLEAVED_MEM_OPS
9426  case Opcode::kSimd128LoadPairDeinterleave:
9427  return Cast<Simd128LoadPairDeinterleaveOp>().Effects();
9428 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WASM_DEINTERLEAVED_MEM_OPS
9429 #if V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
9430  case Opcode::kSimd256LoadTransform:
9431  return Cast<Simd256LoadTransformOp>().Effects();
9432 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
9433 #endif
9434  default:
9435  UNREACHABLE();
9436  }
9437 }
9438 
9439 // static
9440 inline size_t Operation::StorageSlotCount(Opcode opcode, size_t input_count) {
9441  size_t size = kOperationSizeDividedBySizeofOpIndexTable[OpcodeIndex(opcode)];
9442  constexpr size_t r = sizeof(OperationStorageSlot) / sizeof(OpIndex);
9443  static_assert(sizeof(OperationStorageSlot) % sizeof(OpIndex) == 0);
9444  return std::max<size_t>(2, (r - 1 + size + input_count) / r);
9445 }

9448  return op.Is<FrameStateOp>() || op.outputs_rep().size() > 0;
9449 }
