9477 bool IsUnlikelySuccessor(const Block* block, const Block* successor,
9478  const Graph& graph);
9479 
9480 // Analyzers should skip (= ignore) operations for which ShouldSkipOperation
9481 // returns true. This happens for:
9482 // - DeadOp: this means that a previous Analyzer decided that this operation is
9483 // dead.
9484 // - Operations that are not RequiredWhenUnused, and whose saturated_use_count
9485 // is 0: this corresponds to pure operations that have no uses.
9486 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE V8_INLINE bool ShouldSkipOperation(const Operation& op) {
9487  if (op.Is<DeadOp>()) return true;
9488  return op.saturated_use_count.IsZero() && !op.IsRequiredWhenUnused();
9489 }
9490 
9491 namespace detail {
9492 // Defining `input_count` to compute the number of OpIndex inputs of an
9493 // operation.
9494 
9495 // There is one overload for each possible type of parameters for all
9496 // Operations rather than a default generic overload, so that we don't
9497 // accidentally forget some types (eg, if a new Operation takes its inputs as a
9498 // std::vector<OpIndex>, we shouldn't count this as "0 inputs because it's
9499 // neither raw OpIndex nor base::Vector<OpIndex>", which a generic overload
9500 // might do).
9501 
9502 // Base case
9503 constexpr size_t input_count() { return 0; }
9504 
9505 // All parameters that are not OpIndex and should thus not count towards the
9506 // "input_count" of the operations.
9507 template <typename T>
9508 constexpr size_t input_count(T)
9509  requires(std::is_enum_v<T> || std::is_integral_v<T> ||
9510  std::is_floating_point_v<T>)
9511 {
9512  return 0;
9513 }
9514 // TODO(42203211): The first parameter should be just DirectHandle<T> and
9515 // MaybeDirectHandle<T> but now it does not compile with implicit Handle to
9516 // DirectHandle conversions.
9517 template <template <typename> typename HandleType, typename T>
9518 constexpr size_t input_count(const HandleType<T>)
9519  requires(std::disjunction_v<
9520  std::is_convertible<HandleType<T>, DirectHandle<T>>,
9521  std::is_convertible<HandleType<T>, MaybeDirectHandle<T>>>)
9522 {
9523  return 0;
9524 }
9525 template <typename T>
9526 constexpr size_t input_count(const base::Flags<T>) {
9527  return 0;
9528 }
9529 constexpr size_t input_count(const Block*) { return 0; }
9530 constexpr size_t input_count(const TSCallDescriptor*) { return 0; }
9531 constexpr size_t input_count(const char*) { return 0; }
9532 constexpr size_t input_count(const DeoptimizeParameters*) { return 0; }
9533 constexpr size_t input_count(const FastApiCallParameters*) { return 0; }
9534 constexpr size_t input_count(const FrameStateData*) { return 0; }
9535 constexpr size_t input_count(const base::Vector<SwitchOp::Case>) { return 0; }
9536 constexpr size_t input_count(LoadOp::Kind) { return 0; }
9537 constexpr size_t input_count(RegisterRepresentation) { return 0; }
9538 constexpr size_t input_count(MemoryRepresentation) { return 0; }
9539 constexpr size_t input_count(OpEffects) { return 0; }
9540 constexpr size_t input_count(ExternalPointerTagRange) { return 0; }
9541 inline size_t input_count(const ElementsTransition) { return 0; }
9542 inline size_t input_count(const ElementsTransitionWithMultipleSources) {
9543  return 0;
9544 }
9545 inline size_t input_count(const FeedbackSource) { return 0; }
9546 inline size_t input_count(const ZoneRefSet<Map>) { return 0; }
9547 inline size_t input_count(ConstantOp::Storage) { return 0; }
9548 inline size_t input_count(Type) { return 0; }
9549 inline size_t input_count(base::Vector<const RegisterRepresentation>) {
9550  return 0;
9551 }
9552 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
9553 constexpr size_t input_count(const wasm::WasmGlobal*) { return 0; }
9554 constexpr size_t input_count(const wasm::StructType*) { return 0; }
9555 constexpr size_t input_count(const wasm::ArrayType*) { return 0; }
9556 constexpr size_t input_count(wasm::ValueType) { return 0; }
9557 constexpr size_t input_count(WasmTypeCheckConfig) { return 0; }
9558 constexpr size_t input_count(wasm::ModuleTypeIndex) { return 0; }
9559 constexpr size_t input_count(std::optional<AtomicMemoryOrder>) { return 0; }
9560 
9561 #endif
9562 
9563 // All parameters that are OpIndex-like (ie, OpIndex, and OpIndex containers)
9564 constexpr size_t input_count(OpIndex) { return 1; }
9565 constexpr size_t input_count(OptionalOpIndex) { return 1; }
9566 constexpr size_t input_count(base::Vector<const OpIndex> inputs) {
9567  return inputs.size();
9568 }
9569 template <typename T>
9570 constexpr size_t input_count(base::Vector<const V<T>> inputs) {
9571  return inputs.size();
9572 }
9573 } // namespace detail
9574 
9575 template <typename Op, typename... Args>
9576 Op* CreateOperation(base::SmallVector<OperationStorageSlot, 32>& storage,
9577  Args... args) {
9578  size_t input_count = (0 + ... + detail::input_count(args));
9579  size_t size = Operation::StorageSlotCount(Op::opcode, input_count);
9580  storage.resize(size);
9581  Op* op = new (storage.data()) Op(args...);
9582  // Checking that the {input_count} we computed is at least the actual
9583  // input_count of the operation. {input_count} could be greater in the case of
9584  // OptionalOpIndex: they count for 1 input when computing {input_count} here,
9585  // but in Operations, they only count for 1 input when they are valid.
9586  DCHECK_GE(input_count, op->input_count);
9587  return op;
9588 }
9589 
9590 template <typename F>
9591 auto VisitOperation(const Operation& op, F&& f) {
9592  switch (op.opcode) {
9593 #define CASE(name) \
9594  case Opcode::k##name: \
9595  return f(op.Cast<name##Op>());
9596  TURBOSHAFT_OPERATION_LIST(CASE)
9597 #undef CASE
9598  }
9599 }
9600 
9601 // Checking that throwing operations have the required members and options.
9602 namespace details {
9603 
9604 template <typename T, typename Tuple>
9605 struct TupleHasType;
9606 
9607 template <typename T, typename... Ts>
9608 struct TupleHasType<T, std::tuple<Ts...>> {
9609  static constexpr bool value = (std::is_same_v<T, Ts> || ...);
9610 };
9611 
9612 template <typename Op, typename = void>
9613 struct ThrowingOpHasProperMembers : std::false_type {};
9614 template <typename Op>
9615 struct ThrowingOpHasProperMembers<
9616  Op, std::void_t<std::conjunction<decltype(Op::kOutputRepsStorage),
9617  decltype(Op::lazy_deopt_on_throw)>>>
9618  : std::true_type {};
9619 
9620 template <typename Op, typename = void>
9621 struct ThrowingOpHasLazyDeoptOption : std::false_type {};
9622 
9623 template <typename Op>
9624 struct ThrowingOpHasLazyDeoptOption<
9625  Op, std::enable_if_t<TupleHasType<
9626  LazyDeoptOnThrow, decltype(std::declval<Op>().options())>::value>>
9627  : std::true_type {};
9628 
9629 // CallOp has special handling because its outputs_rep are dynamic (and found on
9630 // its call descriptor).
9631 template <>
9632 struct ThrowingOpHasLazyDeoptOption<CallOp, void> : std::true_type {};
9633 template <>
9634 struct ThrowingOpHasProperMembers<CallOp, void> : std::true_type {};
9635 
9636 template <>
9637 struct ThrowingOpHasProperMembers<FastApiCallOp, void> : std::true_type {};
9638 } // namespace details
9639 
9640 #define THROWING_OP_LOOKS_VALID(Name) \
9641  static_assert(details::ThrowingOpHasProperMembers<Name##Op>()); \
9642  static_assert(details::ThrowingOpHasLazyDeoptOption<Name##Op>());
9643 TURBOSHAFT_THROWING_OPERATIONS_LIST(THROWING_OP_LOOKS_VALID)
9644 #undef THROWING_OP_LOOKS_VALID
9645 
9646 } // namespace v8::internal::compiler::turboshaft
9647
